</DOCHDR>
 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Maxwell brothers cleared of fraud</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Maxwell brothers cleared of fraud</b><br><br><br><b><h2>27 January 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Political decision tinged  by vendetta, says Kevin Maxwell</h2><h3> "It will be even harder to get a fair trial. My father is still indicted"  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Clare Dyer</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Kevin Maxwell last night accused the Serious Fraud Office of taking "a political decision tinged with vendetta" in going ahead with a  second trial over the collapse of his late father's publishing empire.  <p>  <p>"This is a political decision by Conservatives who won't be there to pick up the pieces when I am acquitted again," he said.  <p>  <p>He was "absolutely amazed" to learn that he would face another trial which could take another two years to reach a verdict.  <p>  <p>"My attitude is very mixed because on the one hand I take great heart from what happened last week. I didn't go to northern Cyprus,  I gave evidence and I was found to be honest.  <p>  <p>"But I feel now I'm entering into the realms of Kafka. It's a horrendous feeling of having been acquitted and the acquittal counting for  nothing." He vowed to get to the bottom of how the prosecution decision was reached. "We are not going to let this go. We want to know  who made this decision and how they came to it."  <p>  <p>His lawyers would write to the Attorney-General, Sir Nicholas Lyell, he said. "We want an answer. If we're not satisfied and if  we're allowed to, we will go for judicial review."  <p>  <p>The 36-year-old whose wife, Pandora, is expecting her sixth child, said he was "absolutely shocked" to read the press coverage of  his acquittal, which saw it as a failure of the jury system.  <p>  <p>'This was a very impressive jury. I was upset that it counted for nothing. The jury were alert, some even took notes in shorthand.  There were 75 or 76 questions asked by the jury, questions that went to the facts. "I have nothing but admiration for the jury. I was  there because I was charged. They were there because they were doing their civic duty." He pointed out that he was still on legal aid and  predicted that the second trial - without the cost of the investigation which is included in the &#163;25m bill for the first trial - would  cost &#163;10m for the defence and &#163;5m for the Serious Fraud Office.  <p>  <p>"How do they defend the expenditure of money? What new facts are going to come out about the collapse and the roles of the  individuals? We have stood trial, we have given evidence on the most sensitive issues." Mr Maxwell said he had doubted before the first  trial that he could get a fair hearing. "I still think it will be even harder to get a fair trial in this one. My father is still indicted as a  co-conspirator. How are we going to find another group of jurors who say they never heard of him? How much can the state take out of  an individual? How much more do they want - to deprive me of my liberty not now but in two years?" The idea of expert assessors  trying fraud cases filled him with horror. "Who do they want to do it? Do they want banks, who were criticised at the trial, or  accountants, who were criticised at the trial, or City regulators, who were described as useless at the trial?" He would rather have his  honesty decided on by 12 ordinary people. "I will fight this with all the strength I've got."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
