 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Sarah Cook marries Turkish waiter</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Sarah Cook marries Turkish waiter</b><br><br><br><b><h2>23 January 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Inquiry call as girl, 13, 'marries'  waiter after holiday romance  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Alan Watkins</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Police and social services launched an investigation last night after the parents of a 13-year-old Essex girl said they had allowed her  to go through a marriage ceremony in Turkey with a man she met during a family holiday. All the county care agencies expressed their  concern over the welfare of Sarah Cook from Braintree who is said to be living with the family of Musa Komeagae, an 18-year-old  unemployed waiter.  <p>  <p>A spokesman for Essex county council said it was meeting the family yesterday afternoon. "Obviously the girl's welfare is the main  concern. We want to help as much as we can."  <p>  <p>But the Turkish authorities threw doubt over the issue by saying that the ceremony was little more than a religious blessing with no  validity either in Turkey or Britain.  <p>  <p>A spokesman at the Turkish embassy in London said that because of the age of the girl the ceremony was not valid. "Our  understanding is that this was a purely religious ceremony. This does not constitute a valid marriage. There may have been a  misunderstanding by the parents of this girl but the ceremony they attended amounts only to a church blessing of the relationship. It is  not a legal union and they are not married by Turkish law."  <p>  <p>The embassy said that a girl of at least 14 is permitted to marry, subject to the approval of an independent judge and written  approval from parent or guardian. Children aged 15 to 18 are not allowed to marry without permission from a parent.  <p>  <p>Essex police warned the family that they were taking legal advice to see whether any British law had been contravened and the  director of Essex social services, Mike Leadbetter, said he was "deeply shocked" to learn that the girl apparently had parental approval.  <p>  <p>In their account to the Sun, Sarah's parents, Jackie, aged 39, and Adrian, 42, a welder, told how Sarah met Musa when she was only  12 during a holiday at the resort of Alanya last June. When Sarah returned to school she showed her friends a diamond engagement ring  that Musa had given to her. She was "so love sick" that she stayed away from school for six weeks and ran up a &#163;1,500 phone  bill calling Musa up to five times a day. In October she persuaded them to let her fly to Turkey on her own for six weeks. They had flown  out for the ceremony.  <p>  <p>According to the Sun Mrs Cook said: "I don't care what people think about her marrying because she is loved and happy. We speak to  her regularly by telephone and would never let any harm come to her. We are not irresponsible parents."  <p>  <p>At least some of the social agencies had known about the situation since late last year but felt themselves powerless. The county  education authority has been sending school books to Sarah, living in the remote township of Kahramanmaras, to persuade her to  continue her education.  <p>  <p>Teachers and staff at the Tabor high school became alarmed when Sarah failed to return to school in September. The head teacher,  Richard Snelling, said: "She is only a 13-year-old child and I would not describe her as particularly mature."  <p>  <p>Mr Leadbetter said: "It appears that, as the relationship apparently has the approval of her mother and father, there is little we can  do. We have sought advice from the Foreign Office but all the indications are that unless the parents were to complain about the  situation we are unable to act."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
