 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year -  Xhosa chief hunts for head of last Xhosa king in Scotland</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b> Xhosa chief hunts for head of last Xhosa king in Scotland</b><br><br><br><b><h2>2 February 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Pretoria seeks return of human heads from museum  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Beresford</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>South Africa is to demand the return of five human heads discovered in Britain's Natural History Museum.  The preserved heads, complete with original skin and glass eyeballs, are thought to be the remains of Khoisan people killed by British troops in the 19th century.  <p>  <p>The museum has indicated that it is not prepared to surrender them for reburial. But a South African minister, Brigitte Mabanda, says she will fight for their return.  South Africa is seeking the return of remains of indigenous people held in Europe as souvenirs.  <p>  <p>Pretoria asked France this week to hand over the pickled corpse of the 'Hottentot Venus', Saartjie Bartman, kept at the Musee de l'Homme in Paris. And Nicholas Gcaleka, a chief and witchdoctor, is on his way to Scotland, with the blessing of President Mandela, in search of the head of King Hintsa, an ancestor killed by British troops 160 years ago, which he suspects is being held as a trophy.  <p>  <p>The five heads at the Natural History Museum were found in cardboard boxes in a back room by a Cape Town artist, Pippa Skotnes, while preparing an exhibition on the Khoisan people.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
