 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Labour wins Hemsworth by-election, crushing Scargill's New  Socialist Party </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Labour wins Hemsworth by-election, crushing Scargill's New Socialist Party  </b><br><br><br><b><h2>17 February 1996</h2></b><br><h2>RMT leaders split as half join Scargill</h2><h3>Union  defections embarrass Prescott and Knapp  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Seumas Milne</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>More than half the Rail Maritime and Transport Union's national executive have joined Arthur  Scargill's embryonic Socialist Labour Party, raising the possibility that the 68,000-strong RMT could  eventually disaffiliate from Labour in protest against the direction taken by Tony Blair. Seven out of  12 RMT executive members have signed up to the party, with one of the union's two assistant general  secretaries, Bob Crow.  <p>  <p>The party, which is due to have its official founding congress in May, won five per cent of the  vote at the recent Hemworth by-election. The defection of the majority of the RMT's activist leadership  will embarrass Labour's deputy leader, John Prescott, who is an RMT-sponsored MP, and the union's  general secretary, Jimmy Knapp, who remains strongly committed to Labour. There is likely to be a move  at the RMT's annual conference this summer to dissociate the union from new Labour, while stopping  short of an immediate call for disaffiliation.  <p>  <p>The combination of Labour's refusal to commit itself to the renationalisation of rail and the abandonment of its Clause 4 commitment to common ownership -  which is still written into the RMT constitution - has led to particular discontent among RMT  activists. Rail privatisation poses a serious threat to the RMT, which staged the 1994 signalworkers' strikes  and led last year's stoppages on the London Underground.  <p>  <p>"New Labour no longer represents the interests of rail workers or supports the goals set out in our  constitution," a prominent executive member said yesterday. "In the longer term, unless a Labour  government delivers on rail renationalisation, we are bound to reconsider our historic affiliation."  Labour loyalists said yesterday that they would try and flush out the SLP supporters at the union's  conference and commit them to backing the Labour Party. But an attempt to do that at the end of last  year was rejected by two to one by conference delegates.  <p>  <p>In another sign of the potential difficulties raised for unions by the formation of the SLP, a  Transport and General Workers' Union branch in London this week voted to affiliate to the new party.  But a TGWU spokesman said it would be contrary to the terms of the union's national affiliation to  Labour, if not directly ruled out by the TGWU's own constitution. The SLP's initial crop of recruits  has been concentrated among union activists, with the public service union Unison, the building  workers' union Ucatt, the Communication Workers' Union and the TGWU most heavily represented. Its  founding group is holding a series of rallies around the country and a members' conference - at which  the new party's policy positions will start to be agreed - is planned for 2 March in London.   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
