 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year -  Obsessive bird feeder jailed </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b> Obsessive bird feeder jailed </b><br><br><br><b><h2>3 February 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Obsessive bird  feeder jailed  </h2>
  <br><br>      <p>An obsessive pigeon feeder was jailed for 56 days yesterday for repeatedly breaching court orders  by distributing mounds of bread around her south London home.  <p>  <p>Mr Justice Butterfield said at the High Court he was quite satisfied Jean Knowlson, aged 68, had  wholly disregarded an injunction aimed at stopping her behaviour on an almost daily basis. "In my  judgement, no warning, no advice, no threat, is capable of deterring her from continuing to behave in  total disregard of the orders of this court, and, in so doing, to cause grave environmental problems,  considerable distress and potential danger to members of the public."  <p>  <p>Mrs Knowlson listened impassively as the judge said there was no evidence of any mental illness. He  had heard that she was getting through as many as 100 loaves a week and scattering bread "ankle-deep",  often at night, around her home in South Norwood, and other nearby places.  <p>  <p>Mrs Knowlson was sent to Holloway Prison for 28 days last July but freed after four days when she  apologised for her contempt of court and agreed not to distribute bread anywhere in Croydon borough.  She told the court then that she could not resist feeding the pigeons when she "looked at their little  faces".  <p>  <p>Mr Justice Butterfield said yesterday he committed Mrs Knowlson "with great regret", but her  conduct had been "anti-social, dangerous and wholly unjustifiable".  <p>  <p>Mrs Knowlson's counsel, Mark Whalan, said her conduct was obsessive but she had tried to curb the  amount of bread she left on pathways, cutting down from 40 handfuls down both sides to 20 handfuls  down one side.   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
