 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Spaceman Steve Bennett launches sugar-powered  rocket</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Spaceman Steve Bennett launches sugar-powered rocket</b><br><br><br><b><h2>3 February  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Take a pound of sugar, a DIY kit, 17 years of jokes and misfires and the sky's  the limit  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>John Ezard</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Britain's DIY spaceman Steve Bennett trounced sceptics and vindicated years of lonely struggle when  his sugar-powered rocket, Starchaser II, soared 1,890 feet up yesterday over the Northumberland moors.  <p>  <p>It did not reach 3,000 feet as he had planned. "My computer projections must have gone astray", he  said. But it sent his reputation into orbit and set a record as the largest airworthy home-made rocket  built in Europe. Putting a rocket into orbit is Mr Bennett's next project. His triumph follows 17  years of misfires and jokes. Even his wife Adrienne used to tell onlookers at his launches, echoing  Corporal Jones in 'Dad's Army', "Don't panic. If the rocket's parachute should fail, keep watching it  and run as fast as you can".  <p>  <p>Now the way is clear for Mr Bennett, a 31-year-old laboratory technician from Dukinfield, Greater  Manchester, who tests toothpastes and soap powders, to aim at becoming the second designer to send a  British rocket into orbit. He is in an international race with amateurs striving to put their craft  the 50 miles into space which are needed to reach orbit. To do this he will build a new rocket,  Starchaser III. His eventual ambition is to launch himself into space. "The sky is very much the limit. I want to launch Starchaser III within 12 months. I am feeling  very confident," he said.  <p>  <p>In his two dozen rocket launches so far, Mr Bennett has spurned the liquid oxygen fuel often used  by amateur rocketeers. All he will disclose about his own is that it is "sugar mixed with other  chemicals"'. His sponsors for the last year - the sugar multinational Tate and Lyle, were delighted  yesterday at his proof of their old marketing slogan Out Of Sweetness Comes Forth Strength.  <p>  <p>The 21ft Starchaser II was cheered as it rose from a pad in a glow of fire against the snow-covered  hills round Otterburn military training area before vanishing into clouds. Then it split into two  pieces which parachuted back to earth. The flight was to test propulsion systems, parachutes and  on-board computers.  <p>  <p>Mr Bennett, who was inspired by the Thunderbird puppets, had to abort his last launch attempt. He  said, "I'm over the moon with the launch, it went brilliantly. I've spent a lot of blood, time and  sweat on this. Some of my rivals' rockets are more sophisticated - but they don't get them back like I  do."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p><b>NASA</b>  <p>  <p>Employees: 20,624  <br>Budget: $13bn  <br>Fuel: aluminium perchlorate  <br>Altitude reached: typically 180 miles or lower earth orbit.   <br>People put into space: 200+  <p>  <p><b>Mr Bennett</b>  <p>  <p>Employees: one (Steve Bennett)  <br>Budget: several thousand pounds  <br>Fuel: weedkiller, sugar  <br>Altitude reached: 1,890ft  <br>People put into space: none  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
