 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Ticket fraud inquiry involving LTS rail on day of privatisation  </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Ticket fraud inquiry involving LTS rail on day of privatisation </b><br><br><br><b><h2>3 February  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Fraud claim may delay privatised line  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Keith Harper</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Plans for one of the first privately-run rail companies to start operating tomorrow were in doubt  last night after an investigation was launched into allegations that a senior member of the company  was involved in defrauding London Underground.  <p>  <p>Rail sources confirmed that the Association of Train-Operating Companies and the British Railways  Board were examining allegations that LTS Rail, the franchise holders on the London, Tilbury and  Southend line, had been involved in issuing tickets from Fenchurch Street station and then re-issuing  them on the same day at Upminster, which LTS shares with London Underground. London Underground is alleged to have been losing up to &#163;30,000 a month as a result.  <p>  <p>John Welsby, chairman of the British Railways Board, has been informed of the discrepancy, which  came to light earlier this week as LTS prepared to take over commuter services on the newly privatised  line. Last night, LTS officials were unable to confirm whether the company was in a position to be able  to start running the service from 2am tomorrow as scheduled.  <p>  <p>LTS Rail's managing director, Chris Kinchin-Smith said in a statement: "The board was made aware on  Friday of allegations. "The Board is co-operating with the British Railways inquiry into the allegations and until this  inquiry is completed it wouldn't be appropriate to comment further."  <p>  <p>Two other private operators are joining LTS on other parts of British Rail's old system; they are  Stagecoach, which will run trains between Waterloo and the West Country, and Great Western trains,  operating between Paddington and Cornwall, and South Wales.  <p>  <p>* Selling the whole of Railtrack, the state-owned track and signalling authority, would hamper  Labour's plan to expand the rail network as a public service, Brian Wilson, shadow transport minister,  said last night. As the Government prepares to speed up the privatisation of both the track and train  operators, Mr Wilson said that without public ownership a Labour government "would be hamstrung in its  determination to expand and develop the role of the railways".  <p>  <p>He was unable to give a commitment to renationalise Railtrack if the Government went ahead with the  sale of 100 per cent of the company in May as planned, but advised investors to steer clear of this  "high-risk" flotation. His comments underline the difficulties Labour would have in finding the  &#163;2bn-plus that the party would need to buy back Railtrack once it had been transferred to  the private sector.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A><