 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Ticket fraud inquiry involving LTS rail on day of privatisation  </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Ticket fraud inquiry involving LTS rail on day of privatisation </b><br><br><br><b><h2>9 February  1996</h2></b><br><h2>'Ticket fraud' rail firm axed  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Keith Harper</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The private company which had been selected to run the London, Tilbury and Southend railway line  was last night told it had lost the franchise following allegations of ticket fraud.  <p>  <p>Enterprise Rail, the company that should have been running the line from last Sunday, was not  expected to meet the necessary conditions for the transfer from British Rail, the franchise director,  Roger Salmon, said. He would not be completing the franchise agreement, he added. He invited rival  companies that had applied to take over the route to re-tender - and told LTS Rail not to try again.  <p>  <p>The collapse of the bid is a considerable embarrassment to the Government. Brian Wilson, Labour  transport spokesman, said it was a disaster. "The Government is hell-bent on damaging an industry  which needs to be kept intact."  <p>  <p>Enterprise Rail's managing director, Christopher Kinchen-Smith, and its finance director, Roger  Turner, who headed the management buy-out bid, are not implicated in the allegations and are returning  to BR's headquarters for other work. BR is continuing its investigation into allegations which have led to the resignation of the  company's commercial director and the suspension of four members of the staff.  <p>  <p>Mr Salmon may have to wait for the outcome of BR's report and a similar inquiry being conducted by  the railway regulator, John Swift, before making a new appointment from the short list of bidders.  Ministers hope a new company could be operating the LTS line within a month. The most likely are the bus operator Prism, and the Canadian-owned GB Railways. For the moment, a  senior LTS official, David Burton, has been appointed caretaker head of the operation.  <p>  <p>The collapse of the bid will create caution among several leading capital-venture companies, who  until yesterday were supporting Enterprise Rail. The fraud allegations involve about &#163;45,000 in  ticket money, which should have gone to London Transport, but allegedly found its way to LTS.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
