 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Ofsted report reveals nearly half of schools in England are  failing their pupils </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Ofsted report reveals nearly half schools in England are failing their pupils  </b><br><br><br><b><h2>5 February 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Ofsted head renews attack on teachers  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Donald Macleod</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Chris Woodhead, HM Chief Inspector of Schools, will today renew his attack on teachers over poor  education standards when he publishes his annual report.  <p>  <p>But Labour and the teacher unions will seize on evidence of worsening school facilities and book  shortages found by inspectors, and seek to highlight the potential loss of 8,000 more teaching jobs as  a result of the pay settlement to be announced this week.  <p>  <p>The annual report of the Office for Standards in Education will target primary schools for failing  to instil basic literacy and numeracy. Last year inspectors judged a quarter of lessons for five- to  seven-year-olds to be unsatisfactory, rising to one-in-three among teachers of eight- to 11-year-olds.  <p>  <p>But today's report will show some improvement in the number of unsatisfactory primary school  lessons.  <p>  <p>Ofsted's concern about reading and basic maths appeared to be borne out by this year's Key Stage 2  tests, when only half of 11-year-olds reached the expected levels.  <p>  <p>Mr Woodhead is mounting a robust defence of his inspection methods, which teachers have criticised  as negative and "hit-and-run". In tomorrow's Education Guardian he will accuse teachers of being "naive in the extreme" for  believing self-evaluation by schools could replace external inspection. Without Ofsted the public  would be blissfully ignorant of the state of the schools. "Critics in the National Union of Teachers may not like the message of my annual report, that bad  teaching cannot be excused as we work urgently to bring the standard of the poorer schools up to the  level of the best," he said.  <p>  <p>Ofsted inspectors have found increasing resources problems in schools, with half of secondary  schools suffering book shortages and one-in-four with inadequate accommodation, which was hampering  the delivery of the national curriculum.  <p>  <p>David Blunkett, Labour's education spokesman, said: "The issue of resources looks like being  highlighted in the week of the teachers' pay award. Concerns about books and accommodation will need  to be addressed by central government. Ofsted will need to have a look at the effect of funding  settlements on this year and next year in schools."  <p>  <p>He said primary school standards needed a clearer focus and Labour was proposing continuous  assessment, with all pupils set individual targets to work towards. Mr Woodhead has insisted there is no evidence of a link between large classes and achievement.  <p>  <p>Labour says local authorities face a &#163;288m shortfall this year, although ministers insist  there has been a 4.5 per cent increase in money for education and schools should be able to cope. Even if the expected 3.8 per cent pay settlement for teachers is phased over 18 months, many  authorities say they will have to shed teaching posts at a time when pupil numbers are rising.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
