 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Harriet Harman & choice of school</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Harriet Harman and choice of school</b><br><br><br><b><h2>9 February 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Labour in  new school furore  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Hencke</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>A Labour MP yesterday rekindled the embarrassing row over choice in education for Tony Blair by  confirming he had sent his two children to public schools because he was not satisfied with their  progress in the state system. Roger Godsiff, MP for Birmingham Small Heath, said yesterday: "The  education of my children is more important than whether it is a politically correct or incorrect  decision to send them there."  <p>  <p>His support for the private sector came as Brian Wilson, Labour's transport spokesman, was quoted  in the Glasgow Herald as saying "public schools produce more social cripples than any organisation  known to man." This comment caused a row at Prime Minister's question time when Mr Wilson's column was  read out by Sir Malcolm Thornton, Conservative MP for Crosby.   <p>  <p>The disclosure of Mr Godsiff's decision also follows the furore over Harriet Harman, Labour's health spokeswoman, sending her son to a grammar  school. Mr Godsiff, an 11-plus failure who was educated at a comprehensive, said he had sent his  children, Anthony and Carrie, to a primary school in Lewisham, south London, where he has continued to  live since winning the Birmingham seat in 1992.  <p>  <p>"Their progress deteriorated after their headmaster retired," said Mr Godsiff, a 49-year-old former  union official. "I tried to find an alternative state school for both, but it proved very difficult.  "Ultimately I decided to exercise my right as a parent to move them where they could get the education  I wanted them to have. I pay the fees out of my own pocket."  <p>  <p>His son goes to Colfe's School, an independent school whose fees are &#163;4,500 a year. His  daughter goes to Blackheath high school, an independent school with a similar fee level. He is keen on  single sex schools for both. Andrew Hargreaves, Conservative MP for Birmingham Hall Green, said: "I do  not blame Mr Godsiff for exercising his parental choice, but his party would deny others the same  opportunity. "It is a grotesque double standard."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
