 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Lord Brocket gets five years for car fraud</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Lord Brocket gets five years for car fraud</b><br><br><br><b><h2>10 February  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Baron friend of Prince gets five years for car fraud</h2>
<h3>Classic Ferraris and  Maserati were crushed for 4.5m insurance  </h3>  <br>By<b>John Mullin</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Lord Brocket, a sporting friend of the Prince of Wales, last night began a five-year sentence for  his role in a &#163;4.5m classic car fraud. He embarked upon the scam when he ran into financial  troubles, but his estranged wife blew the whistle on him.  <p>  <p>Lord Brocket, aged 43, had pleaded guilty to conspiracy to defraud at Luton crown court last month.  He was on &#163;30,000 bail pending pre-sentence reports, but had been warned he faced a custodial  sentence. He showed no emotion as he was taken to the cells yesterday.   <p>  <p>Brocket, charged under his family name Charles Ronald George Nall-Cain, made insurance claims on four cars which disappeared from  his Hertfordshire estate in May 1991. Their crushed remains were later discovered on the estate and in  a London lock-up.   <p>  <p>Judge Daniel Rodwell QC criticised Brocket for enlisting two estate employees help  in the fraud. Mark Caswell, aged 40, and Stephen Gwyther, aged 41, were each given 21-month jail  terms, suspended for two years. The judge said: "To use the pressure and power he had to make men of  previously good record take part in a criminal operation is quite disgraceful."   <p>  <p>Desmond de Silva QC, representing Brocket, said his client had acted out of panic. He had found himself in financial crisis  in 1990 because of the costs involved in developing the family seat. His collection of classic cars,  once worth &#163;20m, was depreciating, and his eight-year marriage to Isabell Lorenzo, then suffering  drug problems, was falling apart. But the judge said: "It's one of the most long-lasting panic  attacks I have ever heard put forward before me. It stems from October 1990 to July 1994." Brocket,  the third Baron of Brocket, inherited the family's 1,400-acre Brocket Hall estate near Welwyn Garden  City when he was 15. After leaving Eton, he joined the army and served as an officer in the 14/20  Royal Hussars. He had failed to develop it as an up-market conference centre, although it was the  venue for several meetings of European ministers during Britain's presidency of the European Union in  1991.  <p>  <p>Brocket Hall has seen scandal before, if not criminal activity. In the last century, Lady Caroline  Lamb was served up naked in a soup tureen before Melbourne's cabinet. Palmerston was found dead on a  billiard table, apparently after an assignation with a maid.  <p>  <p>Brocket reacted coolly after the disappearance of three vintage Ferraris and a Maserati. As  enthusiasts compared it to the loss of four Picassos, Brocket said: "I am left looking like a complete  idiot."  <p>  <p>He filed a &#163;4.5m insurance claim, almost matching the &#163;5m debts of his company, Brocket Hall Ltd. He had reinsured his collection of 50 cars weeks earlier.  <p>  <p>His wife alerted the family, but was ignored at first because of her drug problem.  <p>  <p>When the insurers, Lloyd's of London and General Accident, refused to pay up, Brocket began legal  proceedings. But he dropped them four weeks before the scheduled start of the case in November 1994,  and both sides agreed to pay their own costs of &#163;500,000. Detectives began an investigation a  year ago.  <p>  <p>His wife divorced him this year, citing her husband's unreasonable behaviour. She wants to start a  new life with their children, heir Alexander, aged 11, Antalya, eight, and four-year-old William, in  Puerto Rico. Brocket wants them to stay in Britain.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
