 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Take That split up</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Take That split up</b><br><br><br><b><h2>14 February 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Take this</h2><h3>Since Robbie  Williams left the top boy band last summer he has spent a six-figure sum trying to become his own man   </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Alex Bellos</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>It was perhaps no coincidence that Take That announced their split at the same time as the Academy  Award nominations were revealed in LA. In terms of back-slapping and cringeing self-indulgence,  yesterday's press conference in Manchester was on a par with the most nauseous Oscar acceptance  speech. Until, that is, a brave journalist mentioned Robbie Williams... Did the panel realise it  was their ex-colleague's birthday? The chirpy banter suddenly became nervous laughter. The tension was  especially revealing as only seconds before, Gary, Mark, Jason and Howard had been lingering on what  great friends they are and were... For a moment the cracks in Take That's carefully crafted image  were there for all to see.  <p>  <p>Robbie is the one man who knows what it is like to leave Take That. He was sacked last summer "for  having an opinion", he believes - for breaking the strict rules that kept the boys in line so the  machine could make its millions. This meant no unofficial snaps, no girlfriends in public and, for a  while, no smoking.  <p>  <p>Robbie's story opens the lid on what it is really like to be part of a boy band. Robbie, a genial  22-year-old, says subtle mind games were used to play on the band members' insecurities so that they  would stick together. He was made to feel useless. "I genuinely believed that I couldn't sing," he  says now, "that I had no talent, I couldn't dance, I had no say and I had no confidence. (Take That)  was always Gary. There was only one person being managed. When it came to being a person, being in  Take That was just total Fantasy Towers."  <p>  <p>The other members, he claims, simply wanted to keep their heads down, make the money and deal with  the emotional issues later. "They were living this formula and I just couldn't do it because I was  becoming a young man. I wanted to live how I wanted to live."   <p>  <p>The final straw was last year's Glastonbury festival last June, at which his antics earned him the tabloid tag Drugs Daft Robbie. He  won the respect of a new community of fans - ravers - but was immediately sacked from Take That. Since  then he has not wanted to speak to the boys. "At the time they sacked me I had to deal with the press  by myself. I had to become a normal person by myself. No one rang me up. It was out of the frying pan  and into the fire."  <p>  <p>The eight months since then have been taken up with a protracted legal battle with his record  company BMG, which will reach the High Court on 26 February. A clause in his contract says he must  stay on the label. His lawyers will be arguing that, as he wants to leave, this amounts to an unfair  restraint of trade.  <p>  <p>Robbie's departure from Take That has only pushed his cred rating higher. The tabloids and the  public seemed to identify with his carefree nature. He was asked to present Channel 4's Big Breakfast  in the autumn, which he did for a short stint. Since then he has been too busy preparing for his case  to concentrate on anything else. He has spent almost all his six-figure earnings on lawyers and can't  afford to buy his own house. He has turned down offers from the tabloids offering &#163;250,000 for  his story and from promoters wanting him to star in a West End musical. All the major record labels  are reportedly queueing up to sign him if he wins the case. He is aware that the odds are stacked  against him - almost every member of a boy band, with the exception of George Michael who has become a  friend, has failed to have a successful solo career.   <p>  <p>He is also aware that he is no musical genius. "I am not a self-contained man like, say, George Michael. He can go into his own studios and write his  own songs. I need help with mine. Obviously there is a shelf life for an artist of my ilk. The sooner  I do something the better."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
