 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Oil tanker Sea Empress founders on rocks off Milford  Haven</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Oil tanker Sea Empress founders on rocks off Milford Haven</b><br><br><br><b><h2>17 February  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Disaster alert after oil spill</h2><h3>Tugs fight to stop slick from tanker polluting  wildlife reserves  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Owen Bowcott</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>A team of four ocean-going tugs was last night battling to keep the stricken Liberian-registered  tanker Sea Empress afloat as oil slicks broken up by high winds threatened wildlife reserves on the  coast of west Wales.   <p>  <p>The tugs were due to be reinforced early today by several other vessels directed  to the scene of the emergency. And by midnight it had become clear that the extent of the pollution  was much worse than had been earlier thought, with estimates of the amount of light crude oil washed  ashore being put at between four and six thousand tonnes. Worst affected were local beaches in and  around the Milford Haven estuary.  <p>  <p>Seven marine pollution control planes sprayed detergent on to a five-mile slick, which was drifting  eastwards. Two teams of divers assessed the vessel's damaged pump room and holed cargo tanks.  <p>  <p>Plans were underway for a smaller 30,000-tonne tanker, Star Bergen, to be brought alongside to  transfer some of the remaining cargo before the Sea Empress was moved into harbour.  <p>  <p>The grounding of the ship beneath St Ann's Head, the second accident in almost exactly the same  spot in the last four months, immediately prompted calls for an inquiry into shipping safety  standards.  <p>  <p>The vessel has no protective outer hull and was manned by a Russian crew working under a foreign  flag of convenience.  <p>  <p>The incident began at 8pm on Thursday when the 147,000-tonne Sea Empress, managed by Glasgow  company Acomarit (UK) Ltd and carrying a local pilot, approached the entrance to Milford Haven in  order to discharge its cargo of North Sea oil at the Texaco refinery.  <p>  <p>The reasons for the accident, in which 6,000 tonnes of oil spilled into the sea, were not clear  last night. The engines and steering gear were reported to have been working until it ran aground.  <p>  <p>Along one stretch of freshwater beach, the slurp of oil sludge smothering the rocks almost drowned  out the roar of the waves. Lying at the mouth of the estuary, the low hull of the Sea Empress was  wallowing in the swell. Teams of Texaco refinery workers spent all day trying to mop up the black  slime which coated the shoreline at Angle Bay and Freshwater. Clean-up teams used generator-powered  cleaners to suck the largest concentration of oil off the beaches, and sheets of gauze to soak up  slicks that had already contaminated the beaches.  <p>  <p>"It's a terrible sight, and once its got on to the rocks there's nothing you can do unless you wash  it back into the water," said one worker. At Angle Bay the noticeboard in the car park declared that  the area was a Site of Special Scientific Interest, "because of the national importance of its geology  and marine wildlife". There was no sign of the cormorants, choughs, puffins or grey seals promised on  the map of local beauty spots. "Potentially, it's disastrous," said Max Wallace at the Friends of the  Earth's office in Wales. "We need to have an inquiry into the radar system which controls the approach  to the port."  <p>  <p>Numast, the National Union of Marine, Aviation and Shipping Transport Officers, said the problem  was partly due to the number of ships working under foreign flags of convenience which were not  subject to sufficient inspection. "We need well-trained and competent people," said a spokesman. John  Brechin, the manager of the shipping company, said: "It's too early to determine the cause of the  accident but we are working closely with the authorities to find out what happened."  <p>  <p>Sir George Young, the Transport Secretary, flew by helicopter over the stranded vessel and was  shown the main oil slick from the air. After a briefing by harbour officials and the anti-pollution  team, Sir George said all available equipment was being brought into the battle.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
