 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Oil tanker Sea Empress founders on rocks off Milford  Haven</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Oil tanker Sea Empress founders on rocks off Milford Haven</b><br><br><br><b><h2>23 February  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Oil slicks threaten up to one million birds arriving for the summer  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Edward Pilkington</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Environmentalists say the Sea Empress disaster could not have occurred at a worse time. Birds  wintering along the Pembrokeshire coastline near the spillage such as red-throated divers, have yet to  fly north, while birds which spend the summer in the area are about to arrive in the region. Up to one  million seabirds are expected in the next few weeks, attracted by the rich food source brought by the  Gulf stream.  <p>  <p>Particularly at risk are the 33,000 pairs of gannets now inhabiting the second largest gannet  colony in the world on Grassholm, a small island west of Skomer, which was surrounded yesterday by a  thin film of oil. In the latest count, 545 birds had been sighted with signs of oil pollution, mainly  along the Milford Haven estuary.  <p>  <p>The Royal Society for the Protection of Birds said even a relatively thin layer of oil on the  water's surface could still kill birds if they ingested it while preening.  <p>  <p>Booms are now being used for the first time to contain the slick, having been frustrated earlier by  poor weather. The booms will be used to catch the oil and pull it out to sea. It will be a high-risk venture that  could backfire - birds sheltering on the island could be frightened off the rocks and into the  polluted water, with fatal consequences.  <p>  <p>An optimistic estimate is that all these clean-up missions will recover 10 per cent of the oil,  leaving at least 60,000 tonnes still at sea.   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
