 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Oil tanker Sea Empress founders on rocks off Milford  Haven</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Oil tanker Sea Empress founders on rocks off Milford Haven</b><br><br><br><b><h2>27 February  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Welsh oil spill 'is being played down'  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Paul Brown</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The oil spill off Milford Haven was far larger and more damaging to wildlife than the authorities  in Wales have admitted and casualties were mounting hourly, the RSPCA said yesterday.  <p>  <p>Stephen Mulholland, head of the RSPCA in Wales, said briefings by officials were "either naive or  designed to mislead". He said: "Since the Sea Empress ran aground over a week ago, some authorities  have routinely played down the scale of the impact of the disaster in carefully stage-managed press  briefings."  <p>  <p>He did not accept the claims that half the leaked oil had evaporated, that very few large  concentrations of oil remained at sea, or that the story was now "good news". In fact the number of  wildlife casualties was rising. At Milford Haven alone 1,300 birds had been brought in for treatment,  including 15 oiled swans. More than 2,500 birds are estimated to have died. "It is already clear that  the spill is substantially larger than so far stated by the authorities and that its effects will be  considerably greater than any present official predictions," he said.  <p>  <p>The National Trust, which owns 95 miles of coast in Wales, joined the criticism and said "a major  crisis is now unfolding before our eyes" as reports came in of a number of new beaches being oiled as  the wind shifted. Worst hit was the Freshwater West beach which in places yesterday was a foot deep in  oil. Because of the change in the wind, Carmarthen Bay was now being badly affected by oil for the  first time.  <p>  <p>There were also 300 dead birds at Stackpole on the western fringe and oil was being funnelled into  the rest of the bay by the wind.  <p>  <p>The worst hit species so far is the common scoter, a small black duck which winters in Carmarthen  Bay. In the last three days 872 oiled ducks have been picked up for treatment, about a fifth of the  population. A new treatment centre for birds is being opened by the RSPCA in Milford Haven today because its  existing facilities at West Hatch in Somerset are overwhelmed.  <p>  <p>Other species taking significant casualties are guillemots, with 500 currently being treated and  red throated divers. About 30 seals were seen swimming in oil off the Skomer Island bird sanctuary.  <p>  <p>So far no oil has come ashore in north Devon, although there have been reports of around 40 oiled  birds found on the mainland beaches. Lundy island, 12 miles off north Devon, Britain's only marine  nature reserve is the nesting ground for thousands of sea birds, which have started to return to its  steep cliffs to breed.  <p>  <p>Conservationists on Lundy were last night bracing themselves for a change in weather conditions  which they fear could drive oil from the Sea Empress back towards the island, and increase the number  of oiled birds.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
