 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year -  IRA bomb explodes near Aldwych</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b> IRA bomb explodes near Aldwych</b><br><br><br><b><h2>19 February 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Bomb blasts  West End  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Sally Weale</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Scotland Yard received no warning of the explosion which happened at 10.38pm on a 171 bus near  theatreland, prompting speculation among security sources that it may have been an IRA "own goal".  There were unconfirmed reports that up to three people may have been killed.  <p>  <p>The IRA normally gives a coded warning, which is known to police beforehand, raising suspicions  that the bombers may have been travelling to a target when the device exploded by accident. The  alternative is that the IRA could have returned to an earlier, more savage style of operation. Six  people were take to St Thomas's Hospital, three with "significant" head injuries. A further two  casualties were taken to University College Hospital where one middle-aged man was "serious but  stable" in intensive care. A younger man was admitted with minor cuts.  <p>  <p>Last night's blast was the second incident in London in three days, raising fresh fears of a return  to a full-scale campaign of terrorist violence on the mainland. On Thursday police made safe an IRA device believed to contain 11lbs of Semtex explosives which had  been left in a telephone box less than a mile from last night's explosion. On 9 February two people  were killed in the Docklands blast.  <p>  <p>The bus was just turning into the Aldwych off the Strand when a blast ripped through it, tearing it  apart. Early reports suggested a taxi driver crashed into the wreckage. The area was sealed off amid  fears of a second device. David Williams, an accident-and-emergency consultant at St Thomas's  hospital, said: "We have taken six casualties, five men and one lady, all relatively young adults,  three with significant head injuries." The three most seriously injured had been on the bus while two  had been in cars ahead of the scene of the explosion. Doctor Williams said all those that had arrived  at St Thomas's were "very deeply shocked".  <p>  <p>The most seriously injured man had "significant facial injuries with arterial bleeding".  <p>  <p>Witness Paul Rowan, aged 31, said: "There was tangled metal and glass everywhere. I could see one  woman lying face down on the ground about 20 yards away. "I was unable to see her face, but there was blood all over the back of her head, and she looked  really seriously injured. People were putting coats over her to keep her warm in the rain, but then we  were moved back."   <p>  <p>A barrister, Bernard Devlin, aged 40, was working in his chambers in the Inner  Temple when the explosion rocked the building. "It was like loud thunder and at first I thought that's  all it was. But then sirens started wailing and it was clear the IRA were back in London."  <p>  <p>Anthony Yates, aged 26, said: "I was walking down the road and I saw a big white flash in the sky.  I looked and then I saw a double-decker bus but there was nothing left of it, it was blown to pieces. "There were three people at least dead. When the bomb went off, a taxi drove into the bus. The  NatWest bank outside is badly hit. The bus driver and the taxi driver both looked dead. There's a guy  lying outside the bus saying 'my legs, my legs'. "There was another guy with blood coming from his jaw. I ran round to help people and saw him lying  down in the road. There was a lot of glass everywhere. It's a complete mess up there."  <p>  <p>The Irish government last night condemned those responsible for the bombing. A statement issued in  Dublin said: "The Taoiseach and Tanaiste and all members of the Government are deeply shocked by this  appalling outrage." The news of the attack will increase the political pressure on John Major to  abandon any hope of bringing Sinn Fein and the other political parties, notably the Unionists, back  together for talks. Hard-line Conservative backbenchers are bound to press for more stringent security  measures and a full-scale ostracisation of the Sinn Fein.  <p>  <p>After the Docklands bomb, in which two people died, Mr Major said there would be no more  ministerial contact with the Sinn Fein until the ceasefire had been restored. However, he spoke of  taking more risks for peace and the strong underlying message was that Sinn Fein still had a chance to  be brought into the talks process.  <p>  <p>Mr Major is due to meet the SDLP leader, John Hume, today to discuss Mr Hume's proposal for a  referendum north and south of the Irish border on opposition to violence and the need for all-party  talks. Mr Major is due tomorrow to meet the leader of the Ulster Unionists, David Trimble.   <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
