 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Peter Thurnham rejects Tory whip</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Peter Thurnham rejects Tory whip</b><br><br><br><b><h2>23 February 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Majority cut to two as Tory quits  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Michael White</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The Tory MP, Peter Thurnham, last night resigned the Conservative whip "to take stock" after weeks of wavering. His decision, following a 70-minute private session with John Major, reduces the Government's majority to two. Mr Thurnham, MP for the highly marginal Bolton North-east since 1983, had expressed deepening disquiet over what he called falling standards in the party and public life even before last week's Scott report.  <p>  <p>But the driving force behind his decision was anger - shared by his wife, Sarah, who also attended last night's meeting with the Prime Minister - that he had not even been shortlisted for the safe vacant seat of Westmorland, where he has a farm. Mr Thurnham looks set to sit as an Independent Conservative as the Eurosceptic, Sir Richard Body, did for most of 1995. Mr Major was said to be "astonished", particularly as he and the MP had agreed to meet again next week after Mr Thurnham had had time to consider what they discussed.  <p>  <p>Tory officials last night put a brave face on the snub to Mr Major. They said that after a frank exchange of views both men had agreed to "think about things over the weekend" and that Mr Thurnham was still in receipt of the Tory whip. But Mr Thurnham later wrote to Mr Major setting out his position.  <p>  <p>Mr Thurnham's known dissatisfaction and the whips' failure to anticipate and placate it are another sign that the Major administration is splitting at the seams. If the South-east Staffordshire byelection is lost, as expected, the Tory majority will come down to one. The defection makes Mr Major even more reliant on the Ulster Unionists in Monday's vote on Scott, and until the election.  <p>  <p>Bolton North-East Conservatives reacted with fury last night, describing Mr Thurnham's move as "betrayal".  <p>  <p>Graham Smith, the constituency agent, said: "People here are very, very cross at what he has done. They have campaigned for him, they have raised money for him and he has gone ahead and done this without any recourse to the association.  <p>  <p>"He has not taken our view into account. He has not even consulted us. He has gone behind our backs and everyone is extremely angry."  <p>  <p>The constituency chairman, Norman Critchley, said: "I think it's disgusting. He has greatly upset the people of Bolton, who deserve better. I don't believe the Scott inquiry is anything to do with it.  <p>  <p>"I am heartbroken frankly, not only for the work my officers have done but heartbroken for all the loyal supporters in Bolton."  <p>  <p>Labour's chief whip, Donald Dewar, said Mr Thurnham was not alone among Tory MPs in his feelings of discontent over the way the party was going. "This is further evidence that the Tory Party is disintegrating under the weight of its own divisions," he said.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
