 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Peter Clowes freed after serving four years of a 10 years sentence </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Peter Clowes freed after serving four years of a 10-year sentence </b><br><br><br><b><h2>23 February 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Swindler put human face on City fraud</h2><h3>Mystery of Clowes' 'fortune' unsolved  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Lisa Buckingham</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Peter Clowes changed the face of City fraud. Until then insider trading had seemed like a victimless crime while losses from the multi-million pound swindles in the Lloyd's of London insurance market had appeared to fall on investors with so much money they should have known better.  <p>  <p>But the Clowes crash in May 1988 took the life savings of small investors, most of whom were elderly  <p>  <p>For the first time there was a human face to scandal in the City. And as thousands of pensioners faced ruin, it emerged that the portly and prematurely grey Clowes had maintained a lifestyle of breathtaking extravagance at their expense.  <p>  <p>The oh-so-ordinary investment salesman had used their nest eggs to buy himself a yacht which had once been owned by Christina Onassis, four personal jets and a helicopter. His property investments included a &#163;600,000 chateau in France and a farm in the Peak district.  <p>  <p>He and his wife Pamela, who was formerly married to Hollies' bass guitarist Eric Haydock, holidayed in the Caribbean, drank Veuve Cliquot and chauffeured themselves around the North-west in a couple of Bentleys and a Porsche.  <p>  <p>But the Clowes' story, which started when he left school at 15 to work in his parents' hardware store before moving on to become an insurance salesman, came to an abrupt halt when the business crashed with &#163;150m of debts.  <p>  <p>Barlow Clowes had been set up in 1973 as a small-scale investment business in partnership with Elizabeth Barlow. She left the company in 1980 when it had about &#163;10m of investments. That swelled to &#163;190m  <p>  <p>with the savings of investors who thought they were putting money into gilts - rock solid government securities - during the next seven years. Clowes had promised them a better than average return. But instead of putting their money into gilts he was exploiting a tax avoidance loophole known as bondwashing which involved cleverly timing the buying and selling of bonds to maximise interest and minimise tax payments.  <p>  <p>This lucrative avenue was closed by the then-chancellor, Nigel Lawson, and a desperate Clowes was forced offshore to hide from regulatory scrutiny. The pressure to provide a growing return to investors as well as funding his increasingly lavish lifestyle prompted him to take over a moribund textile and financial services company called Ferguson which was quoted on the Stock Exhange and could provide him with the credibility he needed. He quickly hit the takeover trail to try to build up income with which to meet his promises to investors. But this manoeuvre depended on Ferguson's share price rising. And that came to a sudden end with Black Monday in October 1987 when stock markets worldwide crashed.  <p>  <p>Barlow Clowes suffered the ignominy of being the first company to be shut down by the new Securities and Investments Board, which had come into being as part of the sweeping changes to City regulation promulgated by the Financial Services Act of 1986.  <p>  <p>But a subsequent investigation by the Parliamentary Ombudsman in 1989 revealed that repeated bungles by the Department of Trade and Industry had allowed Clowes to continue his charmed life when the business should clearly have been closed. The Ombudsman concluded that had the DTI acted in 1985 when it first knew that Barlow Clowes was not maintaining proper records, losses would have been capped at &#163;31m.  <p>  <p>Finally, last year, the full 1,581-page DTI inquiry into the scandal was published. Costing an astounding &#163;6m to produce, the report  <p>  <p>calculated that Clowes had used more than 80 per cent of funds to support himself and his family. He had benefitted personally by some &#163;25. The whereabouts of his alleged personal fortune remains a mystery. The DTI report said Clowes did not act alone. An associate, Guy Cramer, had "a major responsibility" for manipulating investors' funds. Cramer had benefitted "substantially" the inspectors concluded. He was found not guilty in the 1992 trial.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
