 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Peter Clowes freed after serving four years of a 10 years sentence </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Peter Clowes freed after serving four years of a 10-year sentence </b><br><br><br><b><h2>23 February 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Anger after Clowes is freed  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Larry Elliott</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Peter Clowes, who masterminded one of the biggest frauds of the 1980s, was freed on parole by a "reluctant" Michael Howard yesterday after serving four years of a 10-year jail term. The man who swindled 15,500 investors out of their savings left the High Court in London vowing he would clear his name and claiming he was worried that his case had taken on an unhealthy political dimension  <p>  <p>Mr Clowes was released after threatening legal action against the Home Secretary and the chairman of the parole board for failing to consider his plea for early release.  <p>  <p>The Prison Service said later that Mr Howard had reluctantly agreed to parole because Mr Clowes had been sentenced in 1992, before the introduction of tougher rules governing the amount of their sentences that criminals had to serve in prison.  <p>  <p>Mr Clowes had lost an earlier plea for parole when a judge ruled that the Parole Board was entitled to take the view that he needed more time in prison to come to terms with his guilt and "examine his attitude to dishonesty".  <p>  <p>But he withdrew his appeal against that decision last month after Mr Howard and the Parole Board agreed to reconsider his application and give a decision not later than 20 February.  <p>  <p>Investors, who recovered 90 per cent of their investments after a &#163;150m government rescue, reacted angrily last night to the news of Mr Clowes's release, saying that he should have served his full jail term. Politicians also expressed concern that Mr Clowes was free after serving less than half the sentence imposed when he was convicted of stealing &#163;16m from investors following the collapse of the Barlow Clowes investment group in 1988.  <p>  <p>Labour's City spokesman, Alistair Darling, said: "Many victims will be astonished to find he is out after only four years. It makes a mockery of the Government's claims to be tough on City crime."  <p>  <p>David Shaw, the Conservative MP who was a driving force in the campaign to get compensation for Barlow Clowes victims, said: "I think his release is appallingly early. It is difficult enough getting prosecutions, but far too many of these people are getting out before they should. I would have thought six to seven years would have been more appropriate." Mr Clowes continued to maintain his innocence during a BBC radio interview last night. "I reserve the right to challenge my conviction and I still hope and intend to get my conviction quashed. It's far from the end of the matter; this is the beginning of the matter."  <p>  <p>Explaining his concern about the political backdrop to the case, Mr Clowes said: "The situation here is a balancing one between the needs of victims, who rightly feel aggrieved, and the need for justice. I have accepted the justice of this country even though I personally disagreed with it. There was no intention of ever stealing from any investor."  <p>  <p>Mr Clowes, who is barred from holding company directorships until 2007, pledged to work for the return of the 10 per cent which remained unpaid to investors.  <p>  <p>Mr Clowes will be subject to a programme of supervision by the Probation Service and risks being sent back to jail if he breaks any of the conditions attached to his parole.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
