 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Gorbachev comes 92nd in survey of top 100 politicians in Russian paper </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Gorbachev comes 92nd in survey of top 100 politicians in Russian paper </b><br><br><br><b><h2>2 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>'Joint-92nd' Gorbachev dreams optimistically of election triumph  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>James Meek</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>It was like a happy dream of bygone days for Mikhail Gorbachev. There was hardly space to blink amid the mass of journalists squeezed into a tiny room as the last Soviet leader held forth.  <p>  <p>He was loving it. He was world statesman, Nobel prize winner, author, film star, the champion of free peoples everywhere. Would he fight Boris Yeltsin in presidential elections?  <p>  <p>"I will," he said. "I will."  <p>  <p>The trick with dreams is not waking up. When someone asked about the opinion polls, which show that the former Soviet president is supported by half of one per cent of voters, he seemed close to regaining consciousness. But not for long.  <p>  <p>"The latest poll I heard said that the basic mass of people will decide who to vote for in the voting booths," he said. "So let's not be in a hurry." Mr Gorbachev was ostensibly calling for all democratic forces to unite under - or at least alongside - him against his old rival, Mr Yeltsin, and the communist leader Gennady Zyuganov. But if the democrats failed to heed his call, he would fight alone.  <p>  <p>Unless there is an extraordinary shift in mood over the next three months, the former Soviet leader, who is 65 today, has as much chance of becoming president as Leonid Brezhnev.  <p>  <p>A survey of the top 100 politicians in the Nezavisimaya Gazeta newspaper yesterday put Mr Gorbachev in joint 92nd place.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
