 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Neighbours dispute over Flossie the pig costs 35,000</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Neighbours dispute over Flossie the pig costs 35,000</b><br><br><br><b><h2>2 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Judge tells Flossie she'll have to go</h2> <h3>A dispute that has cost a pig's owner more than 35,000  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Martin Wainwright</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Pot-bellied Flossie the pig and her four daily kilos of manure were officially branded a nuisance yesterday, ending a rancorous neighbours' dispute and landing her owner with a bill of more than &#163;35,000. Computer engineer Paul Telford, aged 35, looked incredulous as a county court judge awarded &#163;15,600 damages to his retired neighbour Paul Bray, 62.  <p>  <p>The judge ordered him to pay his costs, estimated at more than &#163;10,000, and those of the Brays, who received legal aid only after using all their savings.  <p>  <p>Mr Telford appeared close to tears as his barrister Philip Walling described the penalty as "astonishing compared with the usual &#163;500 to &#163;1,000", but said immediately that he would not move house. Mr Bray and his wife Mary slipped away after speaking briefly of their hopes of "going home to peace and quiet, a good night's sleep and a nice cup of tea". The fate of 15-stone Flossie, a Vietnamese pot-bellied sow with an impressive range of squeals and smells, was meanwhile the talk of the North-east. The recorder Julian Hallam gave Mr Telford two months to move the animal from the scene of the six-year battle between neighbouring luxury bungalows in Tynemouth.  <p>  <p>The recorder dismissed entirely the picture painted in court of Mr Bray as an obsessive and jealous man who was supposed to have hit back with gallons of dumped wallpaper paste and nuisance calls. He said: "Mr and Mrs Bray could not sleep or enjoy normal lives."  <p>  <p>Mrs Bray's graphic account of Flossie's squeals, pungent dung and ability to attract rats and flies convinced the judge, who also decided that Mr Telford had played tapes in the middle of the night of the Brays' late dog Jet barking. This was reinforced by booming pop music, car revving and the use of industrial compressing machinery.  <p>  <p>Mr Telford, a bachelor, said after the judgment: "I will miss Flossie so much, she has been such a good friend. She has been living in my garden for five years now... I was stunned by the judge's decision and I just want to cry."  <p>  <p>Mrs Bray said after the judgment: "I'm just glad it's all over. What I am looking forward to most is getting a good night's sleep and a nice cup of tea."  <p>  <p>Mr Bray said forgivingly: "I hope that within the time limit Flossie can be found somewhere appropriate to live."  <p>  <p>Both sides thanked reporters after the case. Mr Bray said he appreciated the humour of the daily stories and Mr Telford suggested the press might find Flossie a home.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
