 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Bus bomb in Jerusalem kills 18</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Bus bomb in Jerusalem kills 18</b><br><br><br><b><h2>4 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>'Martyr' leaves perilous legacy  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Derek Brown</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Little is known of Islam Mohammed, the young man who blew himself and 18 others to pieces in Jerusalem yesterday. He was 24, according to Palestine Liberation Organisation sources, and lived in the West Bank town of Hebron. He was, apparently, a former student at the prestigious Bir Zeit university, near Ramallah.  <p>  <p>He was a fanatic supporter of the Islamist movement, Hamas; a victim of an organisation seemingly in an advanced state of disintegration. Hamas and its military wing, Izedeen al-Qassam, have long been described as formidably disciplined and committed to their peculiar vision of an Islamic state of Palestine. But there is mounting evidence that at the political and paramilitary levels, the movement is deeply divided.  <p>  <p>The division is not simply between relative moderates and hardline militants. It is a more complex process of factional dissolution. Last week, the Hamas military wing claimed responsibility for the 25 February suicide bombings in Jerusalem and Ashkelon, which killed 27 people. There were two more statements four days later, the first denying responsibility for the slaughter, the second reiterating that responsibility. On 26 February, an American of Palestinian extraction drove his car into a crowded Jerusalem bus queue, killing a woman before being shot dead by Israeli armed civilians. Two days later, Hamas claimed - in Damascus - that he was yet another "martyr" in the anti-Zionist cause.  <p>  <p>The latest Hamas statement carries the group's hubristic hallmarks, claiming credit for the carnage in Jaffa Street on behalf of "the martyred Engineer Yahya Ayyash". He was the movement's master bombmaker, assassinated by Israeli agents in early January.  <p>  <p>"To the government of Israel: with this attack we end our response to the martyring of the Engineer, and we will halt military activities starting this morning in order to give the Israeli government and the inside (the locally-based) Hamas political leadership time to reach a truce through the mediation of the Palestinian Authority within three months," it said. The gloating tone was genuine enough. The only problem is that last week Hamas had already offered a conditional truce, strongly implying that there would be no more militant attacks before 8 March. Yesterday's bomb made that statement bloodily ridiculous.  <p>  <p>The statement also highlighted the divisions in Hamas by ticking off the authors of the earlier truce offer: "We warn those brothers who issued a leaflet... offering Israel a truce, that they must immediately halt issuing any statements because we have a clear programme and we are committed in front of the world to every word we say."  <p>  <p>The boast carries a chilling message for Israel and the Palestinian Authority. It is that Hamas divided could be a lot more difficult to deal with than Hamas united.  <p>  <p>Mahmoud Zahhar, a Hamas leader, yesterday dismissed a threat by Shimon Peres, the Israeli prime minister, to wage all-out war against the group. "If they force us to drink from this cup, they'll drink from it, too," he said.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
