 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Caroline Beale freed from US jail</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Caroline Beale freed from US jail</b><br><br><br><b><h2>5 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Baby killer freed in US court deal</h2><h3>Mother returning to Britain after plea bargain  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Mark Tran</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Caroline Beale, the woman accused of murdering her newborn baby in a New York hotel room, will return to Britain this week after striking a deal with the US prosecuting authorities.  <p>  <p>Yesterday she was sentenced to eight months in prison - which she has already served - after pleading guilty to second degree manslaughter. The rest of her sentence comprises five years' probation and one year of psychiatric care. Until yesterday, she had consistently maintained that the child was stillborn.  <p>  <p>Ms Beale, aged 31, shook uncontrollably as she took her seat in front of the judge, and answered his questions in a barely audible whisper. The prosecuting attorney, Marjory Fisher, said the case was one of the most tragic in her 13 years as a prosecutor. Citing a psychiatric report, she said Ms Beale, although aware of her action, had suffered from a pre-existing condition - depression - and would need continuing psychiatric therapy and medication.  <p>  <p>Ms Beale is due to fly back on Friday with her parents, and will immediately start psychiatric treatment at the Maudsley hospital in south London. A former Department of Health employee from Chingford, Essex, Ms Beale was arrested in September 1994 at Kennedy Airport, New York, when she, her boyfriend, Paul Faraway, and two of his brothers were about to board a flight to London. The body of her 8lb daughter was concealed beneath her coat.  <p>  <p>She had given birth alone in the bath of a Manhattan hotel room the previous night after hiding her pregnancy from her family, friends and even Mr Faraway, her live-in lover of 12 years.  <p>  <p>Ms Beale and Mr Faraway had taken a holiday in the US to help them recover from the death of a close friend, Alison Taylor, who had desperately wanted children of her own. Ms Taylor had been forced to have her ovaries removed in an attempt to stop the progress of cancer, shortly before Ms Beale became aware she was pregnant. Her death was cited as central to Ms Beale's subsequent depression and psychosis.  <p>  <p>After arrest, Ms Beale was charged with second degree murder - which carries a sentence of between 15 years and life imprisonment - and was sent to New York's Rikers Island prison.  <p>  <p>Eight months later she was granted bail. Her parents, who were by their daughter's side in her last few court appearances, put up their &#163;100,000 London home as part of the bail arrangement.  <p>  <p>After the verdict, Miss Beale declined to answer reporters, except to say that she intended to "learn to speak properly".  <p>  <p>Peter Beale, her father, described the prosecution as "cruel and medieval", while her mother, Daphne, added: "I pity any American girl that gets into this situation because American laws are medieval and should be changed."   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
