 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Caroline Beale freed from US jail</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Caroline Beale freed from US jail</b><br><br><br><b><h2>9 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Jailed mother back home</h2><h3>Legal row rages as woman who tried to smuggle her dead baby out of US enters hospital in Britain  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Eleanor Carty</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Caroline Beale, the British woman who tried to smuggle her dead baby on a flight from New York, last night spent her first night in intensive psychiatric care at Maudsley hospital, south London, after returning from the United States. But the row over her treatment by the US legal system continued.  <p>  <p>Doctors at the Maudsley said she would remain there for at least two weeks, but they were optimistic that she would make a complete recovery from the psychosis that led her to kill her child. Her parents, Peter and Daphne, from Chingford, Essex, will not be able to see her for the time being. Ms Beale, aged 32, was said to be exhausted but relieved to be home after striking a deal with the US authorities. In return for her admitting manslaughter of her baby, Olivia Ann, New York State Supreme Court Judge Robert Hanophy sentenced her to eight months' jail - which she had already served on remand in Riker's Island prison - five years' probation and psychiatric care in Britain for at least a year.  <p>  <p>But the row over her treatment resurfaced at a press conference at the Maudsley yesterday when her new psychiatrist advised against "crowing" over the British legal system. During sentencing on Thursday, the American judge had criticised her father, Peter Beale, for calling the US justice sytem "barbaric and uncivilised" and had called Britain's system, which allows a manslaughter charge for infanticide, primitive.  <p>  <p>Ms Beale's psychiatrist, Professor John Gunn, said: "We in this country have nothing to be crowing about and shouting across the Atlantic about how things are and should be."  <p>  <p>A country that forced jailed pregnant women to give birth in chains had "nothing to tell other countries about the treatment of prisoners". Ms Beale's New York attorney, Michael Dowd, said yesterday there was insufficient evidence to prove the baby was born alive. Ms Beale might have been acquitted of murder at trial, but he persuaded her to admit manslaughter to ensure she could return home.  <p>  <p>He said he was ashamed of the American legal system. "I'm ashamed of our ignorance but I don't think I'm alone. It does the best it can with the laws it has.  <p>  <p>"The best thing I have seen in the past 18 months was the look on her face as the wheels touched the ground in London, knowing she was home," Mr Dowd said. "That was very special to witness."  <p>  <p>Professor Channi Kumar, who had prepared a psychiatric report for her defence, said: "If she is given privacy, she has a very good chance of putting things together. It's going to be difficult but she has shown great resources and I am very optimistic."  <p>  <p>Her time in prison had left her with a condition similar to post-traumatic stress disorder and she still had nightmares. "I visited Riker's myself and I had nightmares about it afterwards," Prof Kumar said. He will oversee Ms Beale's treatment when she is discharged from hospital. She will undergo a course of medication combined with psychotherapy.  <p>  <p>Asked if she would ever be able to form a relationship or have children, Prof Kumar said: "Yes. And if it's in anyone's minds, the chance of such events recurring are virtually nil."  <p>  <p>He said it was important that Ms Beale's baby - who was buried without her knowledge in a pauper's grave in New York - be returned to England. 'That will allow her to grieve for the loss of her baby."  <p>  <p>Arrangements are being made for the return of the child's ashes.   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
