 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Trevor Nunn appointed as director of National Theatre</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Trevor Nunn appointed as director of National Theatre</b><br><br><br><b><h2>7 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>A word from your colleagues, Trevor  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Michael J Ellison</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Stephen Daldry, Royal Court:<br> "Head of the National Theatre is a tremendously difficult job. It has to be an inclusive, not an exclusive organisation, and a variety of tastes have to be reflected in the programming. It must be a shop window, but it must also enable new talent to emerge - in that sense it's got to be a manufacturing business. The director should back his instincts to find the classic works of tomorrow, and make sure the theatre is reinvented for the next generation."  <p>  <p>Adrian Noble, RSC:<br> "The National has to be very involved in developing new writing and drama, as well as the classics, but it should avoid becoming a classical theatre. It's important that the many different strands of British theatre find a voice at the NT, but not in a rigid way. It can't operate to a pre-ordained brief - 15 per cent new writing, 25 per cent populist etc - nor can it proceed by committee. It has to reflect the artistic passions of the man at the helm. There are very few directors who've created entirely new forms of theatre as Trevor Nunn has. His talents are both populist and scholarly."  <p>  <p>Jude Kelly, West Yorkshire Playhouse:<br> "His status will allow the National to continue to attract top artists, which in turn gives him scope to bring on new writers and performers. It's nice to think someone like Trevor is willing to come back into public service."  <p>  <p>Ruth Mackenzie, Nottingham Playhouse:<br> "For the job of artistic director at the National, you should first be brilliant - Trevor Nunn shouldn't find that difficult. Second, be national - something Richard Eyre has been exceptional at. The National has to reach all sorts of audiences. It should be a place where people of all ages and classes can see outstanding theatre. It's important that the NT is full of children and that's a real challenge."  <p>  <p>Rose Fenton , LIFT:<br> "He should bring in more international directors and artists. He should also make more of a link between the National Theatre and the Studio, which is a fantastic resource - as the Royal Court has realised."  <p>  <p>Jenny Topper, Hampstead Theatre:<br> "He has the experience to run a large organisation, and he's one of the best directors we have. There has been speculation about his interest in new writers, but even if he doesn't take an interest he'll appoint someone who will - Howard Davies did this very successfully for him at the RSC."  <p>  <p>Jatinder Verma, Tara Arts:<br> "Trevor Nunn is one of the few directors on record about the need for multi-cultural productions in Britain. He must recognise social changes and reflect them in the theatre so the NT is national in the truest sense - geographically and ethnically."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
