 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Trevor Nunn appointed as director of National  Theatre</TITLE></HEAD> <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea"  vlink="#adeaea"> <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right  BORDER="0"></A> <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br>
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Trevor Nunn appointed  as director of National Theatre</b><br><br><br><b><h2>7 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Stand and  deliver</h2><h3>As Trevor Nunn took to the stand to defend his new appointment as director of  the National Theatre, questions of age and commitment came thick and fast  </h3> <br>By 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Michael J Ellison</b><br><br>      <p> <p>Trevor is teeming and tingling, but that's only to be expected at his age. Another  worrying sign is that he has started quoting from Richard II and is questioning his own sanity.  Well, wouldn't any musicals-made millionaire theatre director who was on the verge of giving it  all up for a pittance of &#163;90,000 a year? Trevor Nunn has been in an institution before,  though he has just tasted a delicious period of freedom roaming the world. But the question of  age persists and even he agrees he should be committed. <p> <p>Sane or otherwise, the man who  looks like Benny from Abba auditioning for the part of a Shakespearean king in blue denims and  brown loafers, has 18 months before he goes back inside. <p> <p>Way before care in the  community was thought of, never mind discredited, he was banged up in the Royal Shakespeare  Company, although he did go on the run a few times. Towards the end of next year he goes back  inside for another stretch, this time in the National Theatre on the south bank of the Thames.  <p> <p>His case was heard yesterday in front of a jury made up mostly of theatre critics of  advanced years. "I'm breathless, not because of my very great age but because I'm excited," he  said folding his hands and fidgeting in a minimalist metal and black plastic seat. <p> <p>"It's  all been rather a pity. I've always been able to be rather discreet about my age. People used  to ask 'What are you going to do when your 40th birthday comes up?' " <p> <p>Anyway, Nunn knows  all about ageism, having tackled it from the other end of the prejudice scale. When he was a  28-year-old slip of a thing at the RSC he had to enthuse actors twice his age and convince  directors that he was a serious proposition. A series of Andrew Lloyd Webber musicals later  they had their answer. <p> <p>And age does have its advantages. For one thing, there's  experience, Nunn's done this sort of thing before, to say nothing of his work in television,  the movies, opera and the West End. After three marriages this "family man by instinct" has  life in perspective, knows it is time to focus on one big task. <p> <p>Then there was the  second item on the charge sheet: commitment. As in, did the globe-trotting director of Sir  Andrew's finest have enough of it to do justice to a five-year contract as the National  Theatre's director? Nunn's defence counsel was having, well, none of that. <p> <p>"I find the  implication of your remark mildly offensive," said the dashing Richard Eyre, bristling above  his black polo-neck. Eyre should know about these things as he will have given his all to the  job by the time he hands over to Trevor after 10 years. It's a little unfair to charge a man  before he's walked out into the street. The most useful adage Brecht ever gave to the theatre  was 'The proof of the pudding is in the eating.'" <p> <p>Shakespeare (of course) and George  Bernard Shaw were the others witnesses subpoenaed from literature in Nunn's defence. Then there  was the chairman of the National's board, Sir Christopher Hogg, erect, debonair, coldly polite,  unforthcoming and deaf to hostile questions. The court wanted to know how old Trevor had got  mixed up in all this. A younger man like Stephen Daldry from the Royal Court or Sam Mendes from  the Donmar Warehouse might have taken the rap. But dark forces had intervened. "I was  approached a few weeks ago and urged to allow myself to become a candidate for this position,"  said Nunn. "I'm disinclined to say who they were. There were several who came from different  aspects of the profession." <p> <p>This, and a promise to mix the esoteric and the populist,  earned him his 18-month suspended sentence reading plays and going to the theatre. "It's  entirely possible that I'm not sufficiently in touch," he confessed. "It's true I've not been  going up and down the country and going to the theatre for the past seven or eight years as I  did previously. That's not to say I'm completely ignorant of what's going on." Yes,  there's more to life than going to the theatre. Eyre spent years making films for television  before taking over the National. "I was a bit dilatory about going to the theatre." <p>  <p>Trevor Nunn is 56. <p> <p> <p> <p> <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td  width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td  width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td  width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td  width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE  height=30 width=400 border=0><tr> <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A  HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td> <td  align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
