 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - New species of bat discovered</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>New species of bat discovered</b><br><br><br><b><h2>6 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Scientists find pipistrelle bats don't mix if they are not on the same wavelength  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Martin Wainwright</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Scientists are poised to confirm the discovery of the first new British mammal for 50 years, once problems with an empty museum cabinet and a headless corpse have been sorted out.  <p>  <p>Radar frequency analysis and a study of breeding habits provide overwhelming evidence that pipistrelle or common bats are two separate species, with similar appearance disguising very different habits.  Examples of the two types were put on fluttering show in a Yorkshire forest yesterday, as mammal specialists celebrated their first addition to the British list since Brandt's bat was shown to be different from the whiskered bat in the early 1950s.  <p>  <p>"This is perhaps even more exciting than that discovery," said John Altringham, a bat specialist at Leeds University, "as the research which separated Brandt's and the whiskered was carried out in Germany. This time, we've done it ourselves."  <p>  <p>The breakthrough was made by Gareth Jones of Bristol University, currently pursuing bats in Malaysia, who discovered that two distinct radar frequencies were used by individual pipistrelles. Most specimens tracked in north Lancashire carried out echo-location on the 55 kilohertz channel, while the majority of Yorkshire bats in Dalby forest, near Scarborough, unvaryingly used 45kHz.  <p>  <p>Dr Altringham, who carried out follow-up studies with doctoral student Kirsty Park, said: "We wanted to see whether bats on the different frequencies ever mated, and they don't. We have not uncovered a single example of 55kHz individuals co-habiting with 45kHz ones."  <p>  <p>The findings have been bolstered by previously unrecognised physical differences. Dr Altringham said: "I have just got to the stage where I can tell you which type a bat is. The 45kHz ones have a slightly more pointed snout and the others have pinker faces."  <p>  <p>Classification experts face a delay in naming the new bat because the original 'type' specimen of Pipistrellus pipistrellus went missing from the Natural History Museum some years ago.  A reserve specimen has lost its head in storage, and scientists are not sure which type it is.  <p>  <p>"It will be a matter of deciding which species is to keep the pipistrellus name and then a new title will be found for the other one," said Dr Altringham.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
