 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Strike by workers at Kew Gardens over pay</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Strike by workers at Kew Gardens over pay</b><br><br><br><b><h2>6 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Pass Notes - No 779: Kew Gardens  </h2>
  <br><br>      <p>Age: About 278 if you are a royal. 155 to you and me. The gardens were only opened to the public in 1841, having previously been a playground for various interchangeable Georges.  <p>  <p>Appearance: Deserted from next Friday if the seeds of discontent are allowed to germinate.  <p>  <p>What? A case of downing trowels? Eighty botanists and horticulturalists say they'll close the garden gates if they don't get a better wage deal. <p>  <p>So they've been made a weedy offer? Their union, the GMB, says the unsettled claim from last year will leave some gardeners with an increase of just one per cent, and even that is performance related.  <p>  <p>Dependent on growth presumably? That sort of thing. But the angry arborealists claim their standard of living is being eroded and that their salaries were blooming useless in the first place.  <p>  <p>It's becoming a bit of a hothouse of militancy then? Hardly fertile ground, there has only been one strike in its history.  <p>  <p>So who propagated that one? Not exactly a grass-roots revolt. August Bank holidaymakers were locked out in 1979 at Kew and Edinburgh, when the members of the Royal Botanic Gardens Constabulary downed handcuffs.  <p>  <p>But surely the back garden of Britain isn't short of a few bob? It got &#163;21m from the Millennium fund in December. Ah, but that's not for wages. It's for a new seed bank to preserve the country's fast-disappearing flora. And it's still looking for another &#163;7m to get the project started.  <p>  <p>But they charge quids to get in these days. Part of public sector pruning. Government cuts took their funding down by a third.  <p>  <p>They've been letting the grass grow under their feet then? Not exactly. It is still home to six million specimens and the last resting place for 3,000 of the world's rarest species.  <p>  <p>Like the breadfruit trees from Tahiti? Those are the ones that Captain Bligh, master of HMS Bounty, was sent to find. They were supposed to be used for cheap food in the slave plantations of the West Indies. And that little episode led to a bit of a mutiny as well, if you remember.  <p>  <p>So instead of being a haven of pastoral peace, it's really seen some stress. If you count George III's 'mad business', yes. He was living there when he was first strait-jacketed  <p>  <p>Not to be confused with: Q-tips, queue this side, B&Q.  <p>  <p>Do say: Great oaks from little acorns grow.  <p>  <p>Don't say: Heigh-ho, it's off to work we go.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
