 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Camelot drops 10 prize for three winning numbers</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Camelot drops 10 prize for three winning numbers</b><br><br><br><b><h2>8 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Lottery change angers bookies</h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Andrew Culf</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>MPs were presented yesterday with a devastating analysis of the impact of the National Lottery on betting and gaming industries as bookmakers stepped up criticisms of Camelot.  William Hill accused the lottery organiser of trying to have a one-way bet by refusing to guarantee the automatic &#163;10 pay-out to players with three winning numbers.  <p>  <p>Members of the Commons national heritage select committee were warned the impact of the lottery meant bookmakers could cut 7,400 jobs and close 2,400 betting shops, while a third of Britain's greyhound tracks could go out of business and 2,500 employees lose their jobs within three years. More than 2,200 jobs have been axed by football pools companies.  <p>  <p>Earlier, Camelot said the move on the &#163;10 prize was a safeguard against a freak result. Most weeks about one million people match three numbers, and three million would have to do so before the &#163;10 prize was suspended. In computer simulations of 279,000 years of lottery draws the so-called "Armageddon scenario" had not happened.  <p>  <p>At question time in the Commons the Prime Minister defended Camelot, saying the chances of someone winning the jackpot were "much greater than the chances of them not being paid &#163;10 for three numbers".  But Jack Cunningham, shadow heritage secretary, said: "The public will understandably be outraged... British people rightly have a clear expectation that prizes will be paid when they win on the lottery." Robert Maclennan, Liberal Democrat heritage spokesman, said: "Camelot makes millions so this miserly move beggars belief."  Graham Sharpe, of William Hill, said: "They are not playing fair. I have never met anyone who backed the winner of the Grand National who has not been paid out."  <p>  <p>Tom Kelly, director general of the Betting Office Licensees Association, told the committee the National Lottery needed a stronger regulator than Oflot, which approved the change. He also said bookmakers wanted a change in the law so they could take side bets on the winning lottery numbers. In Ireland such bets account for seven per cent of the industry's turnover. But Sir John Gorst, Tory MP for Hendon North, asked gambling industry representatives if they were seeking a "cosseted life" because of lottery competition. Mr Kelly said: "All we want is an equal playing field so, product for product, we can match the lottery in order to survive."   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
