 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Jonathan Aitken says ex BMARC chairman, Gerald James should be in "funny farm" </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Jonathan Aitken says ex-BMARC chairman, Gerald James should be in "funny farm" </b><br><br><br><b><h2>7 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Aitken accuses ex-colleague of "fantasy" over arms sales  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Pallister</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Jonathan Aitken, who resigned as chief secretary to the Treasury last year, yesterday launched a vitriolic attack on the former chairman of the defence company, BMARC, which MPs are investigating over the sale of guns to Iran via Singapore.  <p>  <p>Mr Aitken, who was a director of BMARC from 1988 to 1990, told MPs on the Commons trade and industry committee that Gerald James was an obsessive who could not distinguish fact from fantasy. "The conclusion I have come to is that Mr James should be taken off to a funny farm or be charged with perjury, to which he could no doubt successfully plead diminished responsibility," he said.  <p>  <p>It was partly because of Mr James' allegations - that it was well known among BMARC directors that the company's naval cannon were being shipped on to Iran - that the committee was invited to investigate last June by Michael Heseltine, then trade secretary. Mr Heseltine told the Commons that intelligence reports from 1986 to 1988 showed that the final destination of the BMARC weapons "could well have been Iran".  <p>  <p>Mr Aitken, who is involved in legal action against the Guardian, yesterday told MPs he was never informed that the guns were going on to Iran. If he had been told, it would have been like an electric shock. "This story of Gerald James' is completely untrue. It is a lie from start to finish," he said.  <p>  <p>The committee has been told by Mr James and another director that it was common knowledge the guns, made by BMARC under licence from its Swiss parent Oerlikon, were being transferred to Iran. Two other directors have given evidence that they had heard shop-floor rumours about the diversion. All four directors have said they knew the guns were being re-exported elsewhere, but Mr Aitken said he had been told by one of three company executives - he could not remember which - that they could be absorbed by the Singapore navy.  <p>  <p>Mr Aitken was asked by Joan Whalley, Labour MP for Stoke on Trent North, about his experience in the defence field after he said on BBC's Question Time last year: "I don't know the arms trade really at all." He was asked about a letter he sent to Mr James in March 1985, as chairman of Astra Pyrotechnics, in which he offered to help sell the company's military pyrotechnics through "a trusted contact who seems to be able to produce excellent results in both Iraq and Iran".  <p>  <p>Mr Aitken said his friend, Fouad Makhzoumi, "was in the pipe business for sewerage and water. He had many contacts in Iraq and Saudi Arabia. I thought he might be helpful."  <p>  <p>He was also referred to another offer in the letter. Mr Aitken wrote that he was deputy chairman of Security Centres Holdings "which now has a growing business in the field of international defence, military and security training" for special forces in the Middle East. He suggested that the director in charge of that division - a former SAS commander - might use some of Mr James' products.  <p>  <p>Mr Aitken told the committee that Security Centres sold burglar alarms, and the training was for soldiers guarding buildings from terrorist attacks. He said he could not recall newspaper reports about Oerlikon being investigated for illegal arms shipments to Nigeria when he was covering the Biafran civil war as a journalist.  <p>  <p>In his written submission to the committee Mr Aitken said: "I had no knowledge or business experience in Iran." But he admitted to Ms Whalley that he had been a director of a consultancy in the mid-1970s which was involved in laying pipelines in Iran.  <p>  <p>After the hearing Mr James said: "I stand by everything I have said about BMARC and Project Lisi (the code name for the Singapore contract). I think it's a pity that what was supposed to be an independent committee looking into breaches of the export licensing system has developed into a personal attack on me."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
