 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Balliol College accepts money for Flick chair despite  Nazi links </TITLE></HEAD> <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000"  alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea"> <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif"  ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A> <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br>
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Balliol  College accepts money for Flick chair despite Nazi links </b><br><br><br><b><h2>11 March  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Pass Notes - No 781: Balliol College  </h2>
 <br><br>      <p>Age: 733. <p> <p>Appearance: Gothic horror. <p> <p>Pronunciation guide: BAY-LEE-OL. <p>  <p>Status: Oxford University's oldest college (though Merton disputes the claim). <p> <p>Origin  of silly name: Its founder was a nobleman called John de Balliol. <p>  <p>Why did he found it -  scholarly ambition, an interest in rowing? You forget that this was the 13th century, when men  were men and clerics cantankerous. De Balliol had fallen out with the Bishop of Durham, who had  him whipped and demanded an act of charity. De Balliol's response was a house in Oxford for  poor scholars, which his widow Dervorguilla later extended. <p> <p>Adding bar billiards and  table football? That sort of thing. <p>  <p>Any other history? Nothing except drink and theology for  six centuries, until Benjamin Jowett transformed the college in the late 19th century into a  production line for politicians and poets, all characterised by what Asquith - a Jowett protege  - called "effortless superiority". <p>  <p>Fascinating, but is there, as we news hounds say, a peg?  Two. The college is under attack for accepting an endowment from the German Flick family of a  chair in European thought. And Sunday Times columnist Robert Harris has decided that Balliol  man Chris Patten's own brand of "effortless superiority" will be his political undoing. <p>  <p>What's the problem? Naziism. <p> <p>You mean Chris Patten... ? Goodness, no, the very idea,  call the libel lawyer, excise that line. The difficulty lies in the Flick family's history:  Friedrich Flick, who founded the company on which the family fortune is based, armed Hitler in  the Thirties and was jailed for war crimes. Ergo, says agitated alumnus David Selbourne and  others, the money is tainted. <p>  <p>Has Balliol had this problem before? Funnily enough, yes. In the  Eighties Robert Maxwell, whose sons Kevin and Ian both graced the college, endowed a fellowship  in politics. <p> <p>Possible future endowment: The Vincent Jones chair in Peace Studies. <p>  <p>Famous  old boys: Matthew Arnold, Roy Jenkins, Denis Healey, Graham Greene. <p>  <p>Infamous old boy: Drug  trafficker Howard Marks. <p> <p>Mythical old boy: Lord Peter Wimsey. <p> <p>Imperial old girl:  Masako Owada, wife of the crown prince of Japan. <p>  <p>Do say: "Behind every great fortune there is a  great crime" (Balzac). <p>  <p>Don't say: "Didn't Balliol used to have a reputation for radicalism?"  <p> <p> <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td  width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td  width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td  width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td  width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr> <td  align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A  HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=right  valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td> </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
