 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Thomas Hamilton shoots dead 16 children and a teacher in Dunblane </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Thomas Hamilton shoots dead 16 children and a teacher in Dunblane </b><br><br><br><b><h2>15 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Who licensed him to kill?</h2><h3>Hamilton had six gun permits and was known to the police and politicians after pervert allegations  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Sarah Boseley</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Thomas Hamilton, the disgraced scout leader who shot dead 16 small children and their teacher on Wednesday, held firearms certificates for two rifles as well as the four handguns found amid the bodies when the slaughter in the primary school gym finally stopped, it emerged yesterday.  <p>  <p>As a senior Scottish judge was appointed to head an inquiry encompassing everything from school security to tighter firearms controls, the Scottish Secretary, Michael Forsyth, revealed that Hamilton was first granted a gun licence in 1977.  <p>  <p>At the time of the Dunblane massacre, which ended when Hamilton turned a weapon on himself, he was authorised to keep two .357mm revolvers and two 9mm pistols, believed to be the weapons recovered at the scene of the shooting. He was also allowed to keep a 7.6mm rifle and a .22mm rifle, but he was not thought to own either at that time.  <p>  <p>As it began to be questioned how this man could possibly have cleared the hurdle required under the Firearms Act 1968, which states that police must be convinced an applicant is not "of intemperate habits or unsound mind or... for any reason unfitted to be entrusted with a firearm", an extraordinary insight into his thinking was provided by the arrival at television stations and newspapers of letters he had written to the Queen, the Scottish Secretary and others.  <p>  <p>Copies of seven letters, posted the day before the killings, revealed Hamilton's obsession with clearing his name of any sexual perversion. Writing to Mr Forsyth, he accused "over-zealous police officers from Central Scotland Police, obsessed with child abuse, [of] carrying out their failed pervert hunt using unfair tactics".  <p>  <p>In his letter to the Queen written a week ago, he accuses the Scottish Scout Association of passing on the information "that I was a pervert" to the public in an underhand manner.  <p>  <p>Writing to the education convenor of Central regional council in January, he said: "At Dunblane primary school where teachers have contaminated all of the older boys with this poison, even former cleaners and dinner ladies have been told by teachers at school that I am a pervert."  <p>  <p>It also emerged that one mother went to police in 1989 with accusations about Hamilton's sexual activities during a summer camp her son had attended. Later, she says, Hamilton threatened her with a shotgun. When she complained again to the police, she was told the man had a licence for the weapon.  <p>  <p>Last night Scottish police were withholding details of the killings at Dunblane Primary School on the grounds that the matter is sub-judice. Police practice in Scotland, where contempt of court laws are more rigorously enforced than in England, is to say as little as possible while any court case or fatal accident inquiry is pending.  <p>  <p>Lawyers questioned whether prejudice could arise, since the inquiry would be conducted by a judge without a jury. Juries, which sit in many high profile inquests in England and Wales, have been abolished in fatal accident inquiries.  <p>  <p>The three children most seriously injured in the shooting are still critically ill in Glasgow's Yorkhill hospital. One boy, who was shot three times, went through emergency surgery yesterday and is on a ventilator. Another boy, aged five, has multiple wounds and is expected to be operated on later today. The third child, a girl, has a fractured thigh bone. Two children who spent the night in Falkirk hospital were allowed home, while five at the Stirling Royal Infirmary, together with two teachers, were making good progress.  <p>  <p>The headmaster of Dunblane Primary School described yesterday for the first time how he ran to the school gym to find a scene of carnage. Ron Taylor, aged 45, who was first at the scene of the killings, said: "Evil visited us. We don't know why, we don't understand it, and I guess we never will." At Westminster, after a Prime Minister's question time entirely given over to expressions of sorrow and dismay, Mr Forsyth announced the appointment of Lord Cullen, who chaired the investigation into the Piper Alpha disaster, to head the Dunblane inquiry, which will be held in public.  <p>  <p>Calls for further restrictions on gun ownership were muted, due to the atmosphere of mourning in the Commons, but signalled the likely pressures to come.  <p>  <p>Sir David Steel, the former Liberal leader, asked Mr Major if further steps to prevent "the madness of yesterday" could not be taken by adopting proposals from the Firearms Consultative Committee. These include tighter controls on gun clubs and the introduction of the 'good character' test when granting gun licences.  <p>  <p>In an unusual gesture, John Major and Tony Blair will visit Dunblane together this morning. The Queen and Princess Royal will make the journey on Monday.  <p>  <p>MPs in the Commons listened in a rare silence as the Prime Minister spoke of "the almost unimaginable horror" of what had happened and the Labour leader - evidently emotional - asked: "How many parents last night will have clutched their own children to them, imagining the pain which for others is all too real."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
