 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - New scare as govt admit link between CJD deaths and eating BSE-infected meat </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>New scare as government admits link between CJD deaths and eating BSE-infected meat </b><br><br><br><b><h2>26 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Seriously ill 'suspects' studied - Youth link in doubt  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Paul Brown</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Two cases of suspected Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease which could be linked to beef are being studied by the Government's panel, its chairman, John Pattison, said yesterday.  <p>  <p>"They are still alive and it's very difficult for me to talk about the details," he said. An examination of a tiny piece of brain tissue of one of the victims had proved negative, but this did not in itself rule out CJD. Both were seriously ill and confirmation that the disease was the same was not possible until they died.  <p>  <p>Professor Pattison also said that some of the victims of the new strain of fatal brain disorder which may be a human version of 'mad cow disease' were under 10 when they were infected.  Revealing the ages of the 10 victims for the first time, Professor Pattison said the youngest was 18 at the time of death. The others were aged 19, 20, three were 29, two were 30, one was 31 and the last 41.  <p>  <p>The assumption must be that the incubation period was 10 years and the victims had been infected in the mid-1980s. This coincided with the time the bovine form of the disease showed itself.  He said it was the extreme youth of the victims at the time of infection which led the Spongiform Encephalopathy Advisory Committee to consider whether children might be particularly at risk. The normal form of CJD generally affected people over 50. After exhaustive evidence at the two-day meeting the answer was 'no'.  <p>  <p>Professor Pattison said that the advice to government remained the same as the previous week. It was unclear why no cases of the previously unrecognised variant had been found in older patients but that did not mean that younger people were more susceptible.  It could mean that the dietary habits of older people were different or that the disease had been passed off as dementia.  <p>  <p>In contrast to the more robust statements of the two ministers at the press conference, the professor continued to be cautious.  He said that a large number of tests were being carried out and it would be weeks and sometimes months before all the results were available. The most likely cause of the new human form of CJD was eating beef but there was still no proof. Other possible explanations had not stood scientific scrutiny.  <p>  <p>Asked about whether milk and dairy products were safe, Professor Pattison said there was no evidence that they could be a route of infection. He was not so sure about beef. Since muscle contained some nerve tissue then it was a possible route but no evidence had been found.  If there was transmission through beef then it was probably through splashing of offal on to meat in the slaughtering process. The committee wanted measures to make sure offal was removed.  The committee also wanted the Government to ensure that fertiliser derived from animal blood and offal should not be put on fields where animals would graze.  <p>  <p>* Richard Lacey, a Leeds University professor of microbiology in the vanguard of warnings about BSE, suggested putting the age of cattle on packets of beef would help customers avoid the risk of eating BSE-infected meat.  He said on BBC1's consumer programme Watchdog: "The only thing that might matter is the age of the animal from which the beef has come. If they put on the packet the animal slaughtered was aged one or one-and-a-half, that would be much better than age seven."  <p>  <p>Professor Lacey, who has warned BSE-related diseases could spread from animals to humans since the late 1980s, added most beef products come from older animals, the ones most at risk.  <p>  <p>He said the statement by the Health Secretary Stephen Dorrell was meaningless. "I presume it might mean that one burger is safe, 10 - probably safe, 100 - probably safe, 1,000 - might be dangerous."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
