HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Date: Sat, 22 Feb 1997 17:57:04 GMT
Server: Apache/1.1.3
Content-type: text/html
Content-length: 6159
Last-modified: Fri, 31 Jan 1997 13:25:09 GMT
</DOCHDR>
 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - New scare as govt admit link between CJD deaths and eating BSE-infected meat </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>New scare as government admits link between CJD deaths and eating BSE-infected meat </b><br><br><br><b><h2>26 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>In a stew about beef  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Richard Doughty</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Ten years after the first case of mad cow disease (BSE) was identified in Britain, the Government last week announced that there may be a link with the human illness, Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (CJD).  <p>  <p><b>What is mad cow disease?</b>  <p>  <p>Mad cow disease (bovine spongiform encephalopathy) was first identified by scientists in 1986, following the death in 1985 of a previously healthy Holstein dairy cow on a British farm. It had suddenly become edgy and unable to control its movements. Scientists later found that its brain was full of holes, like a sponge.  <p>  <p><b>How widespread is the disease?</b><p>By 1987 there were 20 cases of BSE and by mid-1988 731 cases on 590 farms across Britain and the Channel Islands. By 1991 there were 1,500 cases a week; numbers are currently 300 a week.  <p>  <p><b>Where does it come from?</b>  <p>  <p>No one knows exactly, but the now outlawed practice of feeding cattle with the treated carcases of other animals, including sheep, is thought by many to have caused BSE in cows. The disease is similar to scrapie, a disease that affects sheep's brains.  <p>  <p>In the 1970s and 1980s animal feed manufacturers were adding animal remains and fishmeal to cattle feeds in order to boost their protein content. Sheep remains were used in greater quantities in the early 1980s, when the price of fishmeal rose sharply.  <p>  <p>Scientists believe that cattle ate feed infected with scrapie, and contracted BSE as a result.  <p>  <p><b>How is BSE connected with CJD?</b>  <p>  <p>BSE also closely resembles CJD, a fatal human disease, with symptoms including depression, loss of balance, uncontrolled body movement and loss of memory. Some scientists believe that, in the same way as cattle have contracted BSE by eating sheep infected with scrapie, so some humans could have contracted CJD by eating beef infected with BSE.  <p>  <p><b>What is known about CJD?</b>  <p>  <p>Until recently CJD has been a rare disease which kills about one person in a million, as far as doctors know. It has tended to affect older people and is one of a group of diseases which involves the degeneration of the nerve cells and the production of deposits of prime protein. In CJD this happens in the brain.  <p>  <p><b>What has the Government done to prevent the spread of BSE?</b>  <p>  <p>In 1988 the Government set up a committee to assess BSE, which led to a law requiring the slaughter of all infected animals. But after its investigation, the committee said it was most unlikely that BSE would affect humans. In 1989 the Government introduced a ban on offal sales but until last week ministers were saying that there was no conceivable risk in eating beef.  <p>  <p><b>Why are people getting so worried at the moment?</b>  <p>  <p>New research by a group of specialists into the deaths from CJD of 10 people, who were younger than the usual age of CJD victims, has concluded that it is likely that these cases are linked to exposure to BSE before the introduction of the Government's 1989 offal ban. Experiments have now shown that BSE is only found in the brain and spinal cord, not muscle. Nevertheless anyone who ate beef offal in the years before 1989 may be at risk of contracting the disease. The incubation for the disease is between five and 15 years, so we may be seeing the first few cases of an epidemic.   <p>  <p><b>What is the Government doing now?</b>  <p>  <p>The Government has now announced special regulations for cutting up carcases of cattle aged over 30 months; banned all meat and bonemeal in feed for farm animals; and set up an immediate &#163;4.5m research programme into possible links between BSE and CJD.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
