 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - 1st patient fitted with artificial heart, Abel Goodman dies</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>First patient fitted with artificial heart, Abel Goodman dies</b><br><br><br><b><h2>26 March 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Artificial heart man dies</h2><h3>Procedure thrown into doubt after Oxford hospital has to remove pump because of internal bleeding  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Edward Pilkington</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>A man whose doctors claimed he was the first patient in the world to be fitted with a permanent electric heart has died, 30 hours after the battery-powered pump was removed from his body.  <p>  <p>Surgeons at the John Radcliffe Hospital, Oxford, operated on Abel Goodman on Saturday to take out the device after signs of internal bleeding. The patient's own heart had shown a "remarkable recovery" since the implant five months ago and was considered capable of working alone. However, Mr Goodman, aged 64, died on Sunday night after suffering a "sudden and unpredictable" change in heart rhythm. He leaves a wife and two children.  <p>  <p>Mr Goodman's death is a blow for the hospital, which has been trying to develop an electrically-powered heart as an alternative to human donor organs, which are in short supply. He died four days after a similar heart was implanted in another man at the John Radcliffe. The patient, who has not been identified, was described yesterday as "stable and satisfactory". When Mr Goodman's titanium heart was implanted last October his surgeon, Stephen Westaby, said he could expect a normal life. However, Mr Goodman was plagued by infection and never returned home.  <p>  <p>Mr Goodman, a retired film producer, volunteered to try the new procedure having been told he was too old for a transplant and had six months to live. After the implant he said: "It seemed the only way forward - there was no choice."  <p>  <p>He was the fourth patient to die in Britain after being implanted with an electronic heart. The other three were all treated at Papworth Hospital, Cambridge, which yesterday condemned the John Radcliffe, accusing it of "hype".  <p>  <p>John Wallwork, a heart surgeon who has led Cambridge's research said that, contrary to media reports, it was Papworth that first implanted a permanent artificial heart 18 months ago. Previously, such implants were temporary devices for patients awaiting donor organs.  "The only difference between what we did and what Oxford has done is in the type of pump used. They had a Vauxhall Cavalier, we had a Ford Mondeo - so what?" Mr Wallwork said.  <p>  <p>Papworth made its first permanent trial of the heart on Arthur Cornhill, aged 63, in August 1994. He returned home for several months, but died nine months later.  <p>  <p>Mr Wallwork said Mr Goodman's death underlined the need for a proper trial to evaluate the procedure. Papworth is planning a Europe-wide trial comparing medical treatment of heart patients with the use of mechanical hearts. A further trial is expected soon in the United States.   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
