 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Cunard liner Royal Viking Sun hits a coral reef in Red  Sea</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Cunard liner Royal Viking Sun hits a coral reef in Red Sea</b><br><br><br><b><h2>6 April  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Passengers fly home as holed Cunard liner abandons voyage</h2><h3>Coral reef blamed for  leaving Royal Viking Sun adrift in Red Sea with 950 on board  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>John Duncan</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Fifty-four Britons among the 950 people stranded when the Cunard-owned liner Royal Viking Sun hit a  coral reef in the Red Sea fly home today after an abrupt end to their &#163;21,500 world cruise. Cunard confirmed yesterday that the cruise was being abandoned and compensation would be paid to  passengers for the remainder of the 116-day trip.  <p>  <p>The Britons were among 527 passengers and 450 crew towed into the Egyptian port of Sharm el-Sheikh  after the 37,845-tonne ship hit 'an underwater object' on Thursday night and lost power.  <p>  <p>Passengers had to don lifejackets and go to lifeboat stations after the liner took on water and  began to list. The lifeboats were swung out over the water, but were not needed as water was pumped out and the  crew managed to stabilise the list after an hour, and power up reserve generators. Two tugs were sent  from the Jordanian port of Aqaba. An evacuation ship was also sent but not used.  <p>  <p>Officials at the Mohammed nature reserve, a protected area of coral reefs off the southern tip of  the Sinai peninsula, said radio messages from the ship made clear it had struck coral.  <p>  <p>The incident happened just outside the nature reserve boundaries, and the reserve is sending a team  to assess damage.  <p>  <p>A spokesman from the international control centre in Stavanger, Norway, which co-ordinated the  operation, said: "It must have been frightening for a time."  <p>  <p>The crash tore a three-yard hole in the hull and some water initially went into some cabins. "We felt a jolt, it was a terrible jolt," said Geoff Edwards, a passenger from Palm Springs,  California. "There were a bunch of people singing on stage and they all went down like dominoes.  That's how big a jolt it was." "The passengers are all safe," a Cunard spokesman said. "There are  absolutely no injuries. They are reasonably happy, considering what they have been through."  <p>  <p>The passengers were put up in hotels in Cairo and Sharm el-Sheikh last night.  <p>  <p>Their round-the-world cruise began at Fort Lauderdale, Florida, in early January, and had been due  to end at the same place on 29 April. The voyage was the second failed Cunard cruise for about 120 of  the passengers, who had been aboard the liner Sagafjord last month when an engine room fire left it  drifting in the South China Sea.  <p>  <p>Cunard's public image first took a knock in the QE2's disastrous 'Cruise from Hell' in December  1994. A sailing from Southampton to New York went ahead before a big renovation was completed, and  passengers were left fuming over 'exploding toilets' and corridors that they said looked like building  sites.  <p>  <p>In November Cunard agreed to pay a total of &#163;7.5m in refunds and travel credits to passengers  on that cruise.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p><b>Succession of mishaps undermines cruise firm</b>  <p>  <p>Cunard has run into troubled waters in recent years. The firm reported a &#163;16.5m deficit last year and chief executive Peter Ward warned it is unlikely to break even until 1998. In March, the Norwegian group  Kvaerner bid &#163;904m for Cunard's parent Trafalgar House, sparking speculation that the shipping  company and its flagship QE2 could be put up for sale.  <p>  <p>In February, the liner Sagafjord lost power after a fire in the South China Sea with 500 passengers  on a world cruise. It was towed to the Philippines. Last year port officials in Southampton condemned  food hygiene on board the QE2 after an inspection of the ship's Queen's Grill.  <p>  <p>Cunard was forced to pay &#163;7.5m compensation to QE2 passengers after a trip, dubbed the 'Cruise  from Hell', in December 1994. US coastguards accused the company of putting passengers' lives at risk  during the cruise and said the ship should never have set sail. In 1993, Cunard was fined &#163;1,000  after complaints that a cruise advertised as a two-day trip lasted only 38 hours.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
