 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Noel and Liam's mum defends her sons</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Mrs Gallagher and famous names pledge support for Oasis</b><br><br><br><b><h2>6 April 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Mum sings Oasis stars' praises, no matter what some might say  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Stuart Millar</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>It was an announcement that Oasis stars Liam and Noel Gallagher could have done without. To the dismay of fans, their proud mum yesterday revealed that the icons of bad behaviour were actually sensitive souls who always put their family first.  <p>  <p>Margaret Gallagher leapt to the defence of her sons after Greater Manchester police confirmed they were investigating claims that they used to burgle houses and steal cars before their band took the music world by storm. In an interview with the music paper Melody Maker last month, songwriter and guitarist Noel said: "What people have got to understand is that we are lads. We have burgled houses and nicked car stereos, and we like girls and we swear and we go to the football and take the piss."  <p>  <p>But Mrs Gallagher, who raised her boys single-handed in Burnage, Greater Manchester, insisted they were nice, thoughtful lads who loved their mother. She said she would have known if they had been involved in crime as they had lived at home with her. Noel only moved out when he was 23. "As far as I know they were never involved in any crime. They were just normal boys. "They get a lot of bad publicity. Really they are very thoughtful and kind and all they think about are their family and friends."  <p>  <p>But Sir Wyn Roberts, Tory MP for Conwy, said: "If they are owning up to burgling, perhaps they would help the police by letting them know which houses they burgled."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
