 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Bomber targets Barclays bank</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Bomber targets Barclays bank</b><br><br><br><b><h2>11 April 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Bomber targets  bank</h2><h3> Extortionist with grudge sending homemade devices to Barclays  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Duncan Campbell</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>An extortionist using homemade bombs has been making demands for hundreds of thousands of pounds  from Barclays Bank for the last 16 months, it emerged last night. He has used the phrase 'Welcome to  the Mardi Gras' as his code. Scotland Yard confirmed last night that an extensive investigation into  an obsessive but amateurish bombing campaign has been under way since December 1994. One person has  been injured and no arrests have been made. The demands started with a device being sent to a branch  of Barclays Bank. The extortionist, whose nationality and identity are not known, indicated that he  wanted money to be paid before he would call off his campaign. The bank has not paid any money.  <p>  <p>Some 25 homemade devices have been sent to Barclays branches, and offices and small businesses in  some way connected to the bank. Many of the devices have not exploded. They have been made using a  simple mechanism and some have been hidden inside hollowed-out books. One employee has been injured, suffering slight burns. Remarkably there have been no other  casualties.  <p>  <p>Members of the Anti-Terrorist Branch have been attempting to negotiate with the bomber through the  personal columns of newspapers, including the Daily Telegraph and the Daily Mail. A cat-and-mouse game  has been taking place clandestinely as officers have sought to know more of the reasons for the  demands.  <p>  <p>A police source said it appeared the extortionist had some kind of a grudge against Barclays as the  campaign seemed to be more than an attempt to extract money. Barclays Bank has been attempting to  discover if a disgruntled member of staff, an angry customer, or the relative of a sacked member of  staff could be responsible. The exact total of the money demanded is unclear but it is in six or seven  figures, according to sources. In his first letter the extortionist used the phrase 'Welcome to the  Mardi Gras', which has been used in subsequent correspondence.  <p>  <p>Today's Daily Mirror claims he began his campaign by sending six homemade devices to Barclays  branch managers in early December 1994. Inside the Christmas wrapping paper were video cassette boxes,  each of which concealed a shotgun cartridge springloaded to fire as the box was opened. The paper  claims a woman clerical worker at a branch in Hampstead, north London, was burned on the face and  hands when the box exploded as she unwrapped it. Another worker at a branch in Ladbroke Grove, west  London, was temporarily deafened when the box he was holding detonated in his hands. The other devices  were all defused and taken away for analysis.  <p>  <p>A letter signed Mardine Graham was then received at Barclays headquarters in Northampton, demanding  the bank supply him with credit cards and a means of drawing unlimited sums of money from accounts  which could not be detected. The Mirror claims devices, some containing butane gas cylinders, were  sent to businesses in London, the Midlands and the North. One device was rigged to a phone box in a  busy high street.  <p>  <p>Police sources were last night playing down any similarities with the American 'Unabomber' who has  caused a number of fatalities over the years and has allegedly just been arrested. He too was an  obsessive, although his obsession appeared to be against companies and universities involved with  computers.  <p>  <p>There has been a series of slow and protracted procedures in an attempt to establish a dialogue  with the extortionist. Police had been hoping that details of the investigation would remain secret  until they had a successful conclusion. Most of the targets of the extortionist have been in the  London area or in the Home Counties.  <p>  <p>The operation to trap the extortionist has involved many officers who had spare capacity during the  IRA ceasefire, but clearly now the anti-terrorist branch has other priorities, particularly because  his devices have in some cases been so unsuccessful that no one was aware they were even explosives.  Scotland Yard was unable to comment last night on whether the man was operating alone. "He certainly  has a lot of time on his hands," said one source.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
