 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - BNFL fined 25,000 after worker exposed to  radiation</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>BNFL fined 25,000 after worker exposed to radiation</b><br><br><br><b><h2>13 April  1996</h2></b><br><h2>BNFL fined 25,000 after worker exposed to radiation  </h2>
  <br><br>      <p>The operators of the Sellafield nuclear plant were fined &#163;25,000 yesterday after admitting to  "serious and significant" failures in safety that left a worker contaminated with radioactivity.  <p>  <p>British Nuclear Fuels' system of controlling the amount of contamination from plutonium to which a  contractor was exposed while working in its main fuel separation area had failed, Carlisle crown court  was told. BNFL was also ordered to pay &#163;16,104 costs after admitting a breach of safety  regulations. Henry Globe QC, prosecuting, said it was "fortuitous" that a plater, James Martin, aged  53, had only received a relatively low dose of radioactivity as he replaced bolts on a ventilation duct  without proper protective clothing in June 1994.  <p>  <p>After it was discovered he had become contaminated, changing-room staff wrongly allowed him to put  his radioactive clothing back on before going to the surgery in the Cumbrian reprocessing plant.  <p>  <p>Mr Martin panicked when a checking instrument had "gone off the scale" and suffered episodes of  acute anxiety after the incident, Mr Globe said. In fact the radioactivity he received was only half  the amount of BNFL's annual maximum target for workers and a seventh of the statutory maximum. But Mr  Globe said the subsequent investigation "highlighted a failure by the defendants to take the necessary  and important safety precautions demanded of them."  <p>  <p>Anthony Edwards-Stuart, for the company, said BNFL had introduced an extensive review of training  for contractors. "It is a reflection of the company's serious concern and determination to prevent a  recurrence of incidents such as this," he said.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
