 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Goldfish on display in art exhibition at Tate gallery,  Liverpool </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Goldfish on display in art exhibition at Tate gallery, Liverpool </b><br><br><br><b><h2>19 April  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Lone goldfish causes art world ripples as animal lovers see clear case of cruelty   </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Martyn Halsall</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Dai Vaughan thought the goldfish was rather enjoying the art show. "It's just looking at a lot of  culture vultures as opposed to people slouched in front of the telly," he said. "It looks like a very  happy fish to me." But Maureen Barrett-Spring, an art student in the Sixties, saw the goldfish as victim  of a "cold and pretentious" exhibition. "I don't like living exhibits; it makes me very cross," she  said.  <p>  <p>Other visitors had gone further: the RSPCA confirmed a number of complaints. The animal charity  concluded that the fish was "not necessarily happy (but) is not in a cruel situation," said  spokeswoman Sue Atkinson. The goldfish in question was yesterday still trawling the inside of a glass  suitcase on the floor of the Tate Gallery in Liverpool.   <p>  <p>Across the gallery from its sealed tank stood four other glass suitcases, one on a trolley. They were exhibited by James Chinneck, one of 33  entrants from more than 1,600 submissions for this year's New Contemporaries exhibition. Ms  Barrett-Spring was concerned that the gallery was ignoring the lessons of history. "In Victorian times  they had conversation pieces, but now they call them art," she said. "I think it's the same with this;  it's not art, it's a conversation piece."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
