 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Fetishists march to Downing Street</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Fetishists march to Downing Street</b><br><br><br><b><h2>20 April 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Fetishists  whip up sex freedom drive  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Stuart Millar</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>John Major may be associated with tucking his shirt into his underpants rather than wearing rubber,  but today Britain's growing fetishist population will ask him to repeal a 250-year-old statute which  they say inhibits sexual freedom.  <p>  <p>Groups as diverse as the National Campaign Against the Obscene Publications Act and Feminists for  Free Expression will march through central London to Downing Street to deliver a letter to the Prime  Minister calling for the abolition of the 1751 Disorderly Houses Act.  <p>  <p>They accuse the police of taking a heavy-handed approach to enforcing the act - originally designed  to control prostitution in pubs - which they say has little relevance to fetish clubs in the Nineties.  <p>  <p>The march is being organised by an umbrella body, the Sexual Freedom Coalition, hastily set up last  week after police threats to use the act led to the cancellation of the 10th annual Sex Maniacs Ball  at Brixton Academy. More than 2,000 people were expected to attend the members-only event, which last  year raised more than &#163;15,000 for the Integration Trust, which helps disabled adults to meet  partners.  <p>  <p>Tuppy Owens, the ball's organiser and founder of the Integration Trust, said yesterday the charity  would close unless it was compensated for the loss of revenue. "Obviously it's a disappointment for  the people who lost money on the tickets, but the people in the charity are even more sorry. Our  coffers are now just about empty."  <p>  <p>Ms Owens, author of the annual 'Sex Maniacs Diary' for 22 years and owner of an honorary doctorate  from the Institute for the Advancement of Human Sexuality in San Francisco, said she hoped the ball's  cancellation would force a change in the law. "At a time when fetish clubs are becoming more  mainstream, and more people are getting into them, this act has never been more out of date."  <p>  <p>She admitted she had little confidence that Mr Major would champion their cause, but "I am an  eternal optimist, and I'm sure it's a vote winner." The specialist club scene is enjoying growing  popularity across the country. In London around 10 clubs, catering for sado-masochism,  partner-swapping and fetish wear, run on a regular basis, attracting a diverse clientele. About 3,500  people filled the Hammersmith Palais last year for the highlight of the fetishist calendar, the Skin  Two Rubber Ball.  <p>  <p>But police have continued to raid clubs and bring prosecutions. This month Martin Church, organiser  of the Whiplash club in Putney, west London, was acquitted of offences under the 1751 Act.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
