 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Christopher Robin (Winnie-the-Pooh) dies</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Christopher Robin (Winnie-the-Pooh) dies</b><br><br><br><b><h2>22 April  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Christopher Robin dies, aged 75  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Sue Quinn</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Christopher Robin Milne, confidante of Winnie the Pooh and son of the enchanting bear's creator, AA  Milne, has died at the age of 75. Milne was the inspiration for his father's enduring children's tales  about the little boy, Christopher Robin, his bear with very little brain and his other stuffed toys  which came to life.  <p>  <p>But Milne, whose father in real life was cold and distant, was a reluctant star and spent his life  trying in vain to cast off his image as the golden-haired real-life friend of Pooh. "One day I will write verses about him and see how he likes it," Christopher Milne once said about  his father.  <p>  <p>While the stories for and about him have been essential bedtime reading in British nurseries for  the past 70 years, Milne's relationship with his father was a troubled one. Far from spending hours at his father's knee, the young Milne was taken on formal visits to his  parents at mealtimes, spending the rest of his time with a nurse.  <p>  <p>Even for Milne, fact and fiction blurred. He could not remember which of the events recounted by  his father were true. Small and shy, he loved to sew and knit and gloried in taking clocks apart. >Sent to boarding school, he learned to box to defend himself against the inevitable taunts from his  schoolmates. He eventually won a scholarship to Trinity College, Cambridge, but dropped out after a  year to join the army. He was wounded in Italy during the second world war, but returned to university  to earn a degree in English.  <p>  <p>Milne eventually opened a bookstore in Dartmouth in 1951. There he endured visits from people  wanting to shake hands with 'the original Christopher Robin' and signed his father's books in return  for donations to the Save the Children charity.  <p>  <p>He married cousin Lesley de Selincourt, with whom he had a daughter, who has cerebral palsy. Both  survive him.  <p>  <p>Milne broke a lifelong silence in 1974 with the first of three autobiographical books, 'The  Enchanted Places'. "When I was three, my father was three," he wrote. "When I was six he was six... he needed me to  escape from being 50."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
