 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Shoko Asahara (Aum cult) goes on trial in Japan</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Aum cult leader Shoko Asahara goes on trial in Japan</b><br><br><br><b><h2>25 April  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Murder trial of doomsday cult leader grips Japan  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Kevin Rafferty</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Shizue Takahashi, whose husband, a deputy station master, died in the sarin gas attack on the Tokyo  underground last year, sobbed as the multiple murder trial of the founder of the Aum Shinrikyo  doomsday cult began yesterday. Chizuo Matsumoto, more commonly known as Shoko Asahara, is charged with  masterminding the terrorist attack during the morning rush hour on 20 March last year in which 12  people died.  <p>  <p>For reasons to do with rules of evidence, Mr Asahara is charged with 11 deaths and more than 3,700  injuries. The names of all 3,700 were read out in court yesterday.  <p>  <p>Mrs Takahashi, whose husband inhaled a fatal dose of the gas as he tried to help passengers  retching and convulsing on the platform of his underground station, felt enraged yesterday as Mr  Asahara sat with eyes closed and showing no emotion. "My husband died a slow, painful death," she said, wiping tears from her eyes. "How could Asahara  just sit there? He didn't even seem to care."   <p>  <p>From the start, it was clear that Mr Asahara sees the case as a test of wills. The four judges refused him permission to wear his robes, so he appeared in a  navy blue tracksuit with his hair tied back in a ponytail. He stumbled into the courtroom as if to  demonstrate his blindness and frailty. When asked to plead on the charges of murder, he told the judges: "I won't speak."  <p>  <p>But he made a rambling statement about founding and leading the Aum cult. "I pity those who do not  know the truth," he said. "I have no comment about things like lack of freedom and pain." Some people  in the court thought it sounded like an message to his followers, of whom about 120 remain in the  headquarters in the shadow of Mount Fuji.  <p>  <p>A total of 12,292 people queued to take part in a computer lottery for the 48 public seats in the  court. All other court hearings were cancelled, and security was tight with more than 2,000 police on  duty. A dozen media helicopters hovered as Mr Asahara was brought to court in a bullet proof coach  flanked by police cars. If convicted he could face death by hanging. The underground gas attack  destroyed Japan's self-confidence that it was the safest country in the world.  <p>  <p>The names of the more than 3,700 victims took six hours to read. In the public gallery Michiko  Hishinuma sobbed as the name of her husband, Tsuneo, was read out. He was a stationmaster who died  trying to remove a parcel of gas from a train.  <p>  <p>There are eight prosecutors and 12 defence lawyers. Mr Asahara's lawyers have asked to remain  anonymous because they do not support Aum. They complained yesterday that the prosecutors had not  disclosed enough evidence, and that public anger made it hard for Mr Asahara to get a fair trial.  There is no jury system in Japan and judges decide the case.   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
