 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Radio 5 Live named UK station of the year in Sony radio awards </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Radio 5 Live named UK station of the year in Sony radio awards </b><br><br><br><b><h2>1 May 1996</h2></b><br><h2>'Radio Bloke' seals BBC day of triumph</h2><h3>5 Live is national station of the year as Virgin pips 'saviour' Evans in Sony awards  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Andrew Culf</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Radio 5 Live, the BBC's news and sports network, was yesterday named national station of the year at the Sony radio awards, the industry's equivalent of the Oscars.  <p>  <p>The two-year-old station beat off competition from the rejuvenated Radio 1, and took five other awards on a day of triumph for BBC radio. The only surprise was the defeat of Chris Evans, hailed as Radio 1's saviour, in the music-based breakfast programme category by Virgin Radio's Russ and Jono's Breakfast Experience, starring Russ Williams and Jonathan Coleman.  <p>  <p>But Evans, who last week renewed his production company's &#163;1.5m contract with Radio 1 for a year, was named national broadcaster of the year for boosting the station's audience share.  <p>  <p>Matthew Bannister, Radio 1 controller, said: "Chris is the most talented broadcaster of his generation and adding a million listeners in just nine months is an extraordinary single-handed achievement."  <p>  <p>Radio 5 Live, which has silenced pre-launch critics who labelled it "Radio Bloke", succeeds Radio 2 as national station of the year. The judges said: "The excellent team of sports presenters deliver clear, exciting and informed broadcasting, so engaging that it makes listeners feel they are actually there at the event itself."  <p>  <p>The triumph was hailed by controller Jenny Abramsky, who said: "We now have a station which is both fun and of the highest quality, reporting to the whole of the UK."  <p>  <p>The station's awards included two for coverage of last year's Ryder Cup golf, which was otherwise available only on satellite TV.  <p>  <p>Michael Green, acting managing director of BBC Network Radio, said the awards reflected "the great strength in depth of what we do".   <p>  <p><b>Winners</b>  <p>  <p>Documentary: War and Peace (Radio 2); Magazine: Offspring (Radio 4); Comedy: People Like Us (Radio 4); Daytime music sequence: Sounds of the Sixties (Radio 2); Themed music: Fairest Isle (Radio 3); Specialist music: Kershaw in South Africa (Radio 1); Arts programme: Green and Pleasant Land (Radio 2); Drama: Albion Tower (Radio 3); Service to community: Affairs of the Heart (Radio 2); Creativity/innovation: Poetic Theorems (BBC Radio Scotland); Best on-air contest: Apollo 13 (Virgin Radio).  <p>  <p>Best event coverage: Ryder Cup (Radio 5 Live); Best education: The Square on the Pythagoras (Radio 4); Phone-in/debate: Any Questions - Hong Kong (Radio 4); Response to news event: Dallyn on Saturday (Radio 5 Live); Interview: In the Psychiatrist's Chair - Ffyona Campbell (Radio 4); Sports broadcaster: Jonathan Pearce (Capital Gold); Best dramatic performance: Janet McTeer (Radio 4); Broadcaster (local): Steve Penk (Key 103); Local station of year: Moray Firth Radio; Regional station of year: Clyde 1FM; Best radio writer: Lee Hall for I Luv U Jimmy Spud (Radio 4); Radio Academy award: Henry Wood Promenade Concerts.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
