 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Tories suffer heavy losses in local elections</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Tories suffer heavy losses in local elections</b><br><br><br><b><h2>4 May 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Local elections aftermath</h2><h3>Basildon is sole survivor as Essex Man turns back on Tories  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Alex Bellos</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>They used to be the pride of Essex and a symbol of Government electoral success. Now Basildon Conservatives are an endangered species, with only a handful of votes in Thursday's local election keeping them from extinction. As the sole remaining Tory on Basildon's 42-member council, Michael Buckley is aware of the weight on his shoulders. "I intend to rise to the challenge," he says. "A lot of people voted Conservative but didn't get a councillor. I will represent them."  <p>  <p>It is perhaps fitting that the man carrying the Tory torch in an area that did particularly well during the 1980s housing boom is an estate agent. The father of two has lived in Basildon's small neighbour Wickford all his life. After leaving school to work in the City he was tempted back to start selling homes in the county. Rising rates bills in the 1970s ignited interest in Tory policies. He won Wickford's safest Liberal seat by 373 votes in 1988.  <p>  <p>The margin of victory increased to about 2,000 in 1992, when the Tories won control of the council for the first time, shortly after the general election in which Basildon MP David Amess's victory was a vital indicator that John Major would retain power.  <p>  <p>Mr Buckley became deputy leader of the council, although he resigned when he voted against reorganising into a unitary authority. Now after beating a Lib Dem candidate by 99 votes, he is the Conservative group. So is Essex Man's honeymoon with the Tories over? "Essex Man is disillusioned with politicians. The economic indicators are that our support will come back." On a local level, the most pressing issue is the Lib Dems plan to brick-pave Wickford's High Street. He would prefer money going on street-lighting and cameras, but realises that with one versus 41 he faces a near impossible task.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
