 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Star of Bosnia War crimes trial of Dusko Tradic</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Bosnia war crimes trial of Dusko Tradic</b><br><br><br><b><h2>8 May 1996</h2></b><br><h2>"Tadic stood where no man has since Goering and Hess"</h2><h3>The first Bosnian war-crimes trial in the Hague  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Ed Vulliamy</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The Bosnian Serb Dusko Tadic yesterday stood where no man has since Hermann Goering and Rudolf Hess at Nuremberg - charged with "crimes against humanity" as his trial opened in The Hague.  The case before the United Nations war-crimes tribunal is the first in Europe since the Allied court established itself among the ruins of the Third Reich.  <p>  <p>The historic status of the moment was not lost on the prosecution as it opened its case. Grant Niemann QC, of Australia, said the tribunal bore a heavy burden and that "when it is the state that commits the crime, then the community of nations must judge. Otherwise evil has no bounds." At the core of the case is the Omarska concentration camp for Muslim and Croat prisoners, uncovered by the Guardian and ITN in August 1992. There, Mr Tadic was alleged to have been one of the perpetrators of what Mr Niemann yesterday called the most horrific Serbian violence.  <p>  <p>Mr Tadic is the first suspect indicted or held by the tribunal to enter the dock of the special courtroom housed within the headquarters of a Dutch insurance company.  He has pleaded not guilty to a litany of killings, torture, sexual assaults, and other physical and psychological abuse and to persecution. He is accused of playing a pivotal role in the ethnic cleansing that swept across north-western Bosnia during 1992.  <p>  <p>However, Mr Tadic's defence warned that the tribunal was working to rules that have not yet been worked out. His counsel, Michail Wladimiroff, said his client had tried to broker peace in his own village of Kozarac and, having failed, had left to become a traffic policeman in neighbouring Banja Luka.  <p>  <p>Mr Tadic entered court cutting a very different figure to the man who had appeared at pre-trial hearings. He had exchanged his sports jacket and white polo-necked sweater for a solemn navy suit and tie.  <p>  <p>The prosecution outlined the horrors of north-west Bosnia uncovered by "Western media" - the Guardian, ITN and Newsday. First, there was the razing of the mainly Muslim Kozarac, then the infamous camps at Kereterm, Trnopolje and, "the most horrific", Omarska.  <p>  <p>Mr Niemann claimed Mr Tadic was prominent in the story, initially as a fifth columnist who nurtured Muslim friends in Kozarac so as to furnish information to the amassing Serbian army.  <p>  <p>The prosecutor said that, once the destruction of Kozarac was over, columns of Muslims who emerged from their basements with white flags were herded down the main street while Mr Tadic took aside men and shot them. Mr Niemann said there had been a pile of 20 corpses beside the road: all innocent civilians.  <p>  <p>The prosecution claimed that, although he was neither a camp guard nor a commander, Mr Tadic enjoyed a special status which gave him a free run of camps, along with others who were "sadistically predisposed towards violence". Mr Niemann said Mr Tadic, who became a reserve policeman, would arrive at Omarska with lists of names of Muslims singled out for especially brutal treatment.  <p>  <p>In one incident, Mr Tadic was alleged to have forced prisoners to perform oral sex upon each other before they were sexually mutilated. One man was said to have been made to bite off the testicles of another, who died. In Trnopolje, another camp revealed by the Guardian in August 1992, Mr Tadic was alleged to have taken part in the killing of at least 30 prisoners, tortured 12 women and participated in gang rapes.  Mr Tadic is also accused of leading mobs which stormed Muslim villages and killed residents.  <p>  <p>Mr Wladimiroff, a Dutch-Russian, portrayed his client as a victim of mistaken identity, a scapegoat and guinea-pig plucked from the chaos of war. The accused man has sacked two Serbian lawyers in favour of British barristers to assist Mr Wladimiroff. The defence counsel said "the thirst for revenge must not be set aside at the well of polluted justice". He warned of the dangers of high media exposure and low-quality justice. Mr Wladimiroff said: "Dusko Tadic is being promoted as the prototype war criminal. I hold the leaders of all parties in the former Yugoslavia as responsible."  <p>  <p>He questioned the veracity of prisoners due to testify against their alleged torturer. Conditions in the camps "provided the stuff of rumour and the need for a scapegoat".  <p>  <p>The epic trial is expected to last several months, and will bring former camp inmates face-to-face with their alleged torturer.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
