 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Navy admiral, Jeremy Boorda, commits suicide</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Navy admiral, Jeremy Boorda, commits suicide</b><br><br><br><b><h2>17 May 1996</h2></b><br><h2>US navy chief shoots himself  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Martin Walker</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Admiral Jeremy 'Mike' Boorda, the first seaman to rise from the lower deck to become the senior naval officer at the Pentagon, shot and killed himself while sitting on the porch outside his official dwelling yesterday. He had left his office at the Pentagon at lunchtime to return to his quarters at the Washington Navy Yard.  <p>  <p>Adm Boorda, aged 56, was pronounced dead on arrival at a Washington hospital after shooting himself in the chest with a .38 handgun.  There was no immediate explanation for what military police were treating as a suicide. Defence officials said privately that Boorda left at least one note which indicated he took his own life.  <p>  <p>At the time his body was found, the admiral had been scheduled to be interviewed by two Newsweek journalists who were inquiring into his right to the medals he had worn. In the past, Adm Boorda had worn a V-shaped clasp, a special award for valour, and there was some question about the incident for which it was awarded.  <p>  <p>Colleagues were said to be baffled by news of the suicide, although one said Adm Boorda had recently undergone a routine medical exam.  <p>  <p>"His death is a great loss for the navy, for the armed forces and for our country," said President Clinton. "I am personally grateful for the central role he played in planning our mission in Bosnia."  <p>  <p>His closest military confidant, General Philippe Morillon, was clearly distressed at the news and said last night: "He was an extraordinary man, my friend and my guide. I will pray for him and I pay him homage." Adm Boorda joined the navy as an enlisted seaman in 1956, and rose to become chief of naval operations. After combat service in Vietnam, the navy put him through civilian college and through the Naval War College.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
