 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Lord Hanson criticises cynical media for weakening nation</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Lord Hanson criticises cynical media for weakening nation</b><br><br><br><b><h2>17 May 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Cynical media weakening nation, says Hanson  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Alex Bellos</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Sleazy politicians, fat cat businessmen, greedy farmers pah! The real roots of the country's problems are cynical journalists. So says Lord Hanson, the flamboyant business tycoon, who accuses broadsheets and tabloids alike of weakening the nation through lurid disclosures about minor politicians and public figures.  <p>  <p>In a hard-hitting article in the Spectator, he blames journalists for creating the feeling that ours is a time of unprecedented decline. In fact, he states, this picture is wrong: Parliament is relatively uncorrupt, incomes have increased in average real terms and unemployment is lower than in several similar countries.  <p>  <p>"Destructive journalism fosters the belief that politicians routinely evade the truth and break their promises. It creates a climate in which trust in society as a whole dissolves, in which difficulties are magnified beyond all proportion, in which no one is believed to act except for the most self-centred of motives.  In a way this reflects not so much maturity and worldly wisdom on the part of the media reporters, as an immaturity deriving from their never having had to do anything in the real world."  <p>  <p>Lord Hanson, who as chairman of Hanson plc is a regular contributor to Tory coffers, writes that apart from David Frost, Robin Day and Selina Scott, TV journalists treat legislators and business people as "little more than a visiting cabaret".  He adds: "Television exacerbates the concentration on personality and trivia at the expense of serious discussion and analysis. Its tendency to unbalance... tends to destroy public trust."  <p>  <p>He complains that business people are castigated for seeking profit and damaging the environment. "While we hear a great deal about the damaging effects of roads and cars, we hear far less about the enormous strides made by car manufacturers in reducing pollution or about the benefits of better roads, which the hostile critics continue to use, none the less." He says journalists frequently criticise business practices like downsizing and introducing modern industrial methods into underdeveloped countries. "Protests by businessmen that activities of this sort are the conditions for any jobs at all are dismissed with a knowing smile by those who fail to understand that without the profits made by industry, we would have no prosperity, no education, and no quality of life."  <p>  <p>While Lord Hanson has been spared the wost excesses of tabloid intrusion, this can't be said of his late business partner and best friend, Lord White, who died last year. Lord White was a lover of expensive habits and glamorous women.  <p>  <p>Lord Hanson suggests the media had a vested interest in doom-mongering because it made good copy. But in the long run, he says, it damages everybody.  "Cynicism, by its relentless questioning of the character and motives of those at the sharp end of our problems, weakens our nation by turning attention away from what should really be concerning it."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
