 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Life setences for paedophile killers of Daniel Libeskind</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Life sentences for paedophile killers of Daniel Handley</b><br><br><br><b><h2>17 May 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Daniel Handley's killers told they must die in prison</h2><h3>NSPCC calls for national register of convicted child sex offenders  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Duncan Campbell</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Two paedophiles who lived out a fantasy of abducting, sexually abusing and murdering a small boy were given three life sentences each yesterday and told they should die in prison. The case has led to calls for a national register of convicted child sex offenders so their moves can be monitored. Timothy Morss, aged 33, and Brett Tyler, aged 30, both minicab drivers from east London, were convicted at the Old Bailey of the murder of Daniel Handley, aged nine, whom they abducted near his home in Beckton, east London in October 1994. They sexually assaulted him above a minicab office in south London, strangled him and buried him near a golf course outside Bristol. Morss pleaded guilty and Tyler was unanimously found guilty by a jury of four women and eight men after deliberations of less than an hour. He had admitted abducting and buggering Daniel, but not strangling him. The trial judge, Mr Justice Curtis, told the men they were evil vultures who sought to satisfy their lusts on other people's sons.  <p>  <p>"No society can tolerate men abducting a child of that age on a street in broad daylight," he told the two men who stared impassively from the dock. "You are both calculating men and I do not believe you are truly sorry for what you have done."  <p>  <p>He sentenced them both to three concurrent life sentences for murder, buggery and false imprisonment.  <p>  <p>"I propose to recommend that you serve exactly that," said the judge as friends of the Handley family wept in the back of the court. Because of the nature of their offences and "the very, very high risk" they posed to small boys, the judge said the pair should never be released.  <p>  <p>Mr Justice Curtis praised the police, who had tracked Tyler down at a hideout in the Philippines and found Morss after appeals on BBC's 'Crimewatch' programme.  <p>  <p>The judge particularly commended acting Detective Inspector Stephen Kavanagh, who heard Tyler's confession in a videotaped interview in the Philippines, because he had "resisted the temptation to attack a man who most men in the street thought should be attacked".  <p>  <p>He added that the video confession and case papers should never be destroyed and should be shown to anyone who ever thought of releasing the men. After the case, Daniel Handley's mother left the court without comment. She was in distress, and in the company of representatives of the News of the World. The National Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Children also called for a register of convicted child sex abusers. Jim Harding, its director, said: "All relevant voluntary and statutory bodies which work with children should have access to information on the register."  <p>  <p>Both men had been sexually abused from the age of four, and had previous convictions for sex offences involving boys. They had met in a sex offenders' wing in Wormwood Scrubs jail and become lovers. Morss had fantasised about abducting and murdering a small blond boy, and had cruised the streets with Tyler looking for victims.  <p>  <p>A third man, David Guttridge, aged 59, who had been Morss's lover and is also a convicted sex offender, was jailed for 30 months for perverting the course of justice. He had helped Morss flee the country.  <p>    <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
