 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Woman who claimed to have been raped by stalker whilst under police protection in January made story up </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Woman under police protection made up story about rape by stalker </b><br><br><br><b><h2>18 May 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Rape story was false say police  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Duncan Campbell</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>A woman who claimed she had been raped by a stalker while under police protection is now believed to have invented the story.  <p>  <p>Cambridgeshire police spent &#163;200,000 and five months investigating her claims, and were subjected to ridicule because the stalker had apparently struck while officers were supposed to be guarding the woman. The woman, who is not being named, is understood to suffer from a psychiatric disorder and is receiving medical treatment. She will not be prosecuted for wasting police time.  <p>  <p>In January it emerged that the woman, a married mother in her 30s, had told police she had been stalked for months by a man named Chuck. She said he had savagely raped her on 17 January while she was receiving police protection at her home near Huntingdon. A video camera was monitoring the house. An artist's impression of the man was issued and an investigation launched. Calls were made for a change in the law on stalking.  <p>  <p>Yesterday Cambridgeshire's assistant chief constable David Winser said detectives had concluded that the man did not exist and the entire story had been fabricated. The woman had been told of the police's conclusion in the presence of medical help.  <p>  <p>In January, Detective Superintendent Tony Rogers, who led the inquiry, said the woman had been so savagely raped she had not been able to give details for a number of days. Police said yesterday the injuries were minor. Mr Winser said the case papers were passed to the Crown Prosecution Service two weeks ago. It had decided that no action be taken against the woman and the police supported that decision, he said.  <p>  <p>Detectives were puzzled throughout the inquiry that no one else appeared to have any knowledge of the man despite the woman's claims that she had seen him frequently in specific places and that he had telephoned and written to her repeatedly. There was no evidence on the video camera, but it appeared to have been damaged, it was presumed by the stalker. It was now clear that the camera had not been tampered with. However, in the light of the claims of violence and apparent injuries the police had mounted a big investigation.  <p>  <p>"We did not come to this conclusion yesterday," said Mr Winser. "It was during the course of the inquiry, an inquiry that involved a thorough investigation.  It was almost a no-win situation because we had to believe there was a rapist out there," he added. "It is difficult to prove a negative." He said he did not believe the case would make it more difficult for other women to have their claims taken seriously. The police would not name the woman as she was clearly ill. They had ensured she received medical help. "The message we must give out is that offences will be very, very thoroughly investigated," Mr Winser said. "It has involved up to 40 officers at one time and it has taken over five months."  <p>  <p>Ann Neale, of Women Against Rape, said yesterday she hoped the case would not be used to undermine women who already had severe reservations about reporting rape. Only one in 12 rape victims reported the crime.   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
