 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Michael Howard criticised in House of Lords debate by Lord Taylor </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Michael Howard criticised in House of Lords debate by Lord Taylor </b><br><br><br><b><h2>23 May 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Top judge joins attack on Howard  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Alan Travis</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Britain's most senior judge, Lord Taylor, will today launch his most comprehensive onslaught yet on the Home Secretary's new sentencing proposals by warning that they sacrifice justice and are based upon tainted statistics.  <p>  <p>The attack by the Lord Chief Justice, Lord Taylor of Gosforth, who is leaving the post because of illness, marks the deepest breach yet in the constitutional clash between the judiciary and Michael Howard since the Home Secretary unveiled the outlines of his new law and order package at last October's Conservative Party conference.  <p>  <p>Lord Taylor will be backed by a battery of senior judicial figures and former Conservative cabinet ministers when he makes his valedictory attack on the US-style 'three strikes and you're out' minimum sentencing package in a House of Lords debate today.  <p>  <p>Lord Taylor, in an article in the Times, says the Government's criticism of the sentencing record of the courts is wholly unjustified and that the evidence cited by Mr Howard misrepresents the true position. The introduction of minimum sentences of three years for third-time burglars and seven years for third-time drug dealers will 'ratchet up' prison terms for violent criminals as well, and possibly all other prison sentences. It will sharply increase the prison population, above the official forecast of another 10,800.  <p>  <p>His criticism follows a growing chorus of similar warnings from experts, most recently from the new director-general of the Prison Service, Richard Tilt.  <p>  <p>Lord Taylor says that he sees "no merit in adopting a macho attitude regardless of its efficacy" and warns that "certainty in sentencing can only be achieved by sacrificing justice".  <p>  <p>He warns Mr Howard to heed the "humiliating fiasco" which surrounded the 1991 Criminal Justice Act "which collapsed under the weight of its own contradictions". The Government's White Paper, Protecting the Public, published in April, suggests ministers have learned no lessons, he says. Key parts of the 1991 act, including the discredited unit fines system and not taking previous convictions into account when sentencing, were repealed within three years. The Act's underlying presumption of developing alternatives to custody was overturned.  <p>  <p>Lord Taylor goes on to launch a fierce attack on the factual foundations of Mr Howard's policy. The Government's figures showing little difference between average jail sentences for first-time burglars of 16 months and the 19 months handed down third-time offenders are based on flawed evidence, he says.  <p>  <p>The figures quoted in the White Paper were based on a sample of unpublished cases which the courts dealt with in 1993 and 1994. Lord Taylor points out that some of these related to the period when judges where forbidden to take account of previous convictions when sentencing.  <p>  <p>"For the Government to criticise the judiciary for lenient sentencing when they were prevented from taking previous convictions into account by statute is wholly unjustifiable," he writes.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
