 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Elections to all-party talks held in Norther Ireland</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Elections to all-party talks held in Northern Ireland</b><br><br><br><b><h2>28 May 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Ulster parties exchange insults</h2><h3>Sinn Fein branded fascist in forum poll acrimony  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Sharrock</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The Northern Ireland election campaign descended into acrimony yesterday with Unionists rounding on one another, and Sinn Fein labelled 'fascist and sectarian' by the Social Democratic and Labour Party.  <p>  <p>With three days to go before Northern Ireland votes for all-party negotiators and forum members, the Ulster Unionists launched a bitter attack on their rivals the Democratic Unionists, accusing them of undermining their common cause by backing an election system which will divide the pro-union vote among as many as 10 different parties.  <p>  <p>The Ulster Unionists had wanted a proportional representation system - the common method in Ulster - instead of the list system, under which voters vote for a party rather than a candidate. Party leader David Trimble said: "There's a serious danger because of this list system that's been foisted upon us as a result of an unholy alliance between Dr Paisley, (the DUP leader) and Mr Hume, (the SDLP leader)."  <p>  <p>But Ian Paisley immediately countered by accusing Mr Trimble's party of treachery for saying the 1920 Government of Ireland Act - which led to partition - was up for negotiation.  <p>  <p>"The split has come in Unionism because Mr Trimble and Mr Taylor have split away from traditional Unionist philosophy."  <p>  <p>Robert McCartney, UK Unionist MP for North Down, said the Ulster Unionists' failure to grasp an opportunity offered by him to forge a single pro-Union body for the purposes of the elections and thereby avoid the splintering of its vote, was evidence that they were rank amateurs. Mr Trimble had committed an "enormous error of judgment" in the first test of his leadership capabilities.  <p>  <p>In an interview to be broadcast tonight the SDLP MP for West Belfast, Joe Hendron, attacks Sinn Fein, which will be challenging him on Thursday. Dr Hendron, speaking on Irish television, says of Sinn Fein: "They make the odd comment about fellow Protestant Irishmen, but basically they are a sectarian, fascist organisation."  <p>  <p>He believes Gerry Adams is trying to get a permanent peace "but the problem about his organisation, be it Sinn Fein or IRA, is that I don't know who leads whom."  <p>  <p>The Northern Ireland Secretary, Sir Patrick Mayhew, will go to Dublin today to try to resolve differences with the Irish government over the decommissioning of paramilitary weapons once the talks begin. Yesterday senior republican Gerry Kelly said: "No doubt the IRA are watching this as much as any other people involved in this conflict, so let's see what sort of agenda is produced and what attitude is taken to Trimble and his threats, and we will take it from there."  <p>  <p>* Mary Robinson is to visit Britain next week, the first official visit by any Irish president.  <p>    <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
