 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Ariane 5 rocket explodes after launch </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Ariane 5 rocket explodes after launch </b><br><br><br><b><h2>6 June 1996</h2></b><br><h2>French dismiss Ariane setback</h2><h3>Hopes rise for second rocket test as fault is blamed on computer  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Paul Webster</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Despite the spectacular destruction of the Ariane 5 space rocket on its first flight, French officials bullishly declared yesterday that  Europe's satellite launching programme would be back on course soon.  <p>  <p>"This is not a disaster, but rather an incident. It will not delay the second mission for a long time," said Yves Le Gall, head of  strategy at the French space agency CNES.  <p>  <p>A second Ariane 5 is under construction and is due to be launched in the autumn from the European Space Agency (ESA) base at  Kourou, French Guiana, where the first rocket of the series blew itself up on Tuesday 66 seconds after lift-off.  <p>  <p>Experts' confidence that the problem was less serious than expected stemmed from preliminary reports showing it was most likely a  computer software fault that sent the rocket veering off course. This triggered its self-destruct mechanism.  <p>  <p>Ground controllers set off a second explosion to break up the wreckage, scattering debris over land and the Atlantic.  "Something went wrong with the electronic brain which sent the wrong command to the booster engines," one expert said after  studying information sent back from the ill-fated rocket.  <p>  <p>The belief that there was nothing fundamentally wrong with the launcher, which was carrying four uninsured satellites worth about  &#163;500m, has convinced the ESA headquarters in Paris that the second test flight will go ahead as scheduled in late October or  early November.  <p>  <p>References to what is being called a "cerebral accident" have also reassured the French government, which finances 46 per cent of  the Ariane 5 programme, that the consequences were less serious than feared. President Jacques Chirac told cabinet ministers  yesterday he was confident the programme would go ahead as planned.  <p>  <p>The French media were less sanguine, and many criticised the cost of the Ariane programme. The Liberation daily carried the  headline 'The 37 billion franc firework display' next to a picture of the burning debris falling to earth.  <p>  <p>Although the conclusions of an official inquiry will not be known until 15 July, the first analysis was viewed optimistically by the  Ariane 5 development manager, Jacques Durand, who said he believed the initial findings would be proved right.  <p>  <p>"We planned two test launchings and the first has ended in failure," he said. "If a computer fault is confirmed then the problem will be  much easier to solve. The launch programme will continue and when we are ready there will be another blast-off."  <p>  <p>Ariane 5, which has taken 10 years to develop, was intended to maintain Europe's lead in commercial satellite launchings after the  highly successful Ariane 4 was phased out in 1999. Ariane 4, which has ensured ESA about 60 per cent of the international launching  business, has failed only seven times in 86 launchings since 1979.  <p>  <p>But before yesterday's spectacular setback, Ariane 5 scientists predicted a 98.5 per cent success rate for the new rocket,  equivalent to one failure in every 70 attempts.  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
