 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - George Mitchell appointed chairman of Northern Ireland all-party talks </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>George Mitchell appointed chairman of Northern Ireland all-party talks </b><br><br><br><b><h2>6 June 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Pass Notes - No 830: George Mitchell  Age: 62</h2><br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Sharrock</b><br><br>    <p>  <p>Appearance: US version of Sir Patrick Mayhew - definitely very patrician.  <p>  <p>Occupation: As of Monday, Northern Ireland talks chairman.   <p>  <p>Objective: To get his buddy Bill Clinton re-elected... oops, sorry, I mean to end the countless centuries of conflict in Ireland and unite Protestant, Catholic and dissenter in the  bonds of friendship, etc, etc.   <P>  <P>Wow, so everybody must think he's a really great guy?: Nope. Ian Paisley calls him a "sort of Pope" and a "crony of Gerry Adams", which probably has something to do with him having Irish grandparents and encouraging President Clinton to  give Mr Adams a US visa.   <p>  <p>Oh dear, this is the same Ian Paisley who did so well in last week's Northern Ireland elections?: Correct.   <P>  <p>So the ex-senator from New England is of the wrong persuasion?: Well, he was brought up in the Lebanese Christian Maronite town of Waterville, Maine. Work that one out.   <p>  <p>Doesn't Sinn Fein like him?: Apparently not enough to join him at the talks on Monday by getting its military wing, the IRA, to call a ceasefire.   <p>  <p>Aren't these the all-party talks that the Shinners have been demanding for so long and the reason why the IRA called a ceasefire in the first place?: Correct.   <p>  <p>I'm confused: Don't worry, Mr Mitchell will be joining you. There must be historical precedents. Whose boots is Mitchell pulling on?: Well, Gladstone comes to mind. He spent his decling years trying to  solve the Irish question. And, yes, whenever he was getting warm they secretly changed the question.   <p>  <p>The way John Major did?: Well, the Mitchell Commission - set up by Mr Major - reported in January that all-party talks should go ahead asap and the same Mr Major  chose to ignore this advice and call elections instead. And now he's had to call Mitchell back: Yep.   <p>  <p>Why is Mitchell so special?: When he left the Senate after 14 years in 1994, Bill Clinton offered him a seat on the US Supreme Court and he turned it down. Then he was  offered the lucrative job of Commissioner of Baseball - which carried the not insubstantial perk of free tickets to his beloved Boston Red  Sox - and he turned that down too.   <p>  <p>To do what?: To do Bill's Irish work.   <p>  <p>What's likely to be the biggest problem facing him on Monday?: Jatleg.   <p>  <p>Don't you mean jetlag?: This is Belfast, mate, if you can't understand what we're saying you can go and fry yer bap. <p>Least likely  to say: 'Why don't you all just catch yerselves on'.      <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
