 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Violence erupts around the country as England are knocked out of Euro 96 </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Violence erupts around the country as England are knocked out of Euro 96 </b><br><br><br><b><h2>27 June 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Mood turns ugly as fighting fans turn against police  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Owen Bowcott</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Violence erupted in several areas of the country following Britain's defeat, with the worst in London's Trafalgar Square where hundreds of riot and mounted police fought with nearly 1,000 England fans goading officers. By 1am 41 arrests had been made across the capital.  <p>  <p>Reporters and TV crews were attacked in Trafalgar Square. There were 18 casualties treated at the scene. One man was reported to be seriously hurt. The hooligans smashed up cars including a police car. Two cars were set ablaze. Northumberland Avenue was littered with wrecked cars after police cleared the square at around 12.15am.  <p>  <p>Several hundred fans tried repeatedly to break through police cordons to get to Leicester Square and the West End.  German fans skirted the square on their way to Soho, some wearing England hats to avoid attention.  <p>  <p>Hundreds of fans brought mayhem to towns and villages across the Thames Valley, running through streets smashing up cars and shop windows. Police said there had been outbreaks of fighting across the West Midlands. In Brighton, coastguards rescued seven England fans after they leapt off the end of a pier after the defeat.  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
