 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - IRA attack on British army barracks in Germany </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>IRA attack on British army barracks in Germany </b><br><br><br><b><h2>29 June  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Mortars hit British army base</h2><h3>Tactical switch by IRA feared  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Duncan Campbell</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>A British army barracks in Germany was hit by mortar fire last night, raising fears that the IRA  had yet again switched tactics.  <p>  <p>The attack, apparently the first IRA operation in mainland Europe for six years, came as security  sources warned that the IRA was planning to step up operations despite talk of resuming its ceasefire.  The peace process may have been dealt a knock-out blow.  <p>  <p>The mortars were fired at the Quebec barracks in Osnabruck, the largest British army base in  Germany, less than 24 hours after the seven heads of state of the Group of Seven countries issued a  statement condeming terrorism. There were no injuries.  <p>  <p>John Major learned of the news as he sat down to dinner in Lyon. He relayed the news to Germany's  Chancellor Helmut Kohl and US President Bill Clinton. The news seemed to astonish Sinn Fein. But hours  before the attack, Mitchel McLaughlin, the party's chairman, had told a London press conference: "The  IRA cessation is over. They could strike at any time and any place." Although there was no immediate  claim of responsibility, the German authorities were in no doubt the IRA was behind the attack.  Osnabruck, where 4 Armoured Brigade is based, is home to 10,700 military personnel and their families.  The IRA tried to bomb it in 1989 during a three-year terror campaign on mainland Europe.  <p>  <p>German police said last night two mortars exploded in the air. The target appeared to be a petrol  pump. The blast damaged roofs and buildings. The mortars were fired from a Ford Transit van with  British number plates parked 200 yards away at 6.50pm local time. The van was being examined by  forensic experts last night.  <p>  <p>German police said that although three explosions were heard, one mortar was found in the vehicle.  A spokesman said: "We are not sure about the nature of the mortars yet. The two which went off might  have exploded more than once." Lieutenant-Colonel Jan-Dirk Merveldt, a British army spokesman, said:  "At the gates of the barracks there appeared to have been a pantechnicon kind of vehicle which appears  to have let off two mortars into the camp. Apparently one of the projectiles fell near a petrol pump.  There is no fire or anything like that."  <p>  <p>Security sources had been predicting another IRA attack after the Manchester bombing two weeks ago.  They believe the IRA is committed to an extensive campaign and will be varying methods and locations.  <p>  <p>Dick Spring, the Irish deputy Prime Minister, condemned the attack as "an inane act of violence  which will serve no purpose and has no contribution to make to the search for peace". But he said he  would not close the door on Sinn Fein.  <p>  <p>The Irish police a week ago raided an IRA bomb factory in farm buildings at Clonaslee, Co Laois,  and arrested several men, uncovering dozens of mortars which were primed and ready to be used. The  mortars were said to be of a new type.  <p>  <p>The question being asked in Dublin last night was whether the renewed Gardai operations had come  too late, and whether the mortars used in last night's attack had been manufactured in the Clonaslee  factory. Special Branch sources have revealed that during the 17-month ceasefire they were told not to  continue surveillance of IRA suspects.  <p>  <p>If the attack does prove to be the work of the IRA, it may well be the death-knell of the peace  process. From the perspective of Mr Clinton, by whose involvement the republican movement has set so  much store, there would appear to be no further merit in pursuing what, for the foreseeable future, is  a busted foreign policy flush.  <p>  <p>In June 1ast year, four members of an IRA bomb squad were convicted of the attempted bombing of the  Quebec barracks, 135 miles north of Frankfurt, on 19 June 1989. The bombers were disturbed by a night  watchman, and four of the five charges were defused. No one was injured.  <p>  <p>Donna Maguire, one of those convicted, was sentenced to nine years, but was freed as she had spent  nearly six years in jail on remand.  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table><