 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>IRA admits firing three mortars at British army base in Germany </b><br><br><br><b><h2>1 July  1996</h2></b><br><h2>IRA admits firing three mortars at British army base in Germany  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Sue Quinn</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The IRA last night admitted responsibility for the mortar attack on the British army base in  Osnabruck, Germany.  <p>  <p>A coded telephone call to RTE, the Irish Republic's broadcasting network, confirmed the IRA had  launched three bombs at the Quebec base in the group's first assault on British troops in mainland  Europe for more than six years. No one was injured in Friday's attack, which came less than two weeks  after 200 people were hurt in the massive IRA van bombing which devastated a shopping centre in  Manchester.  <p>  <p>The unidentified male caller said: "The attack mounted against the military installation in  Osnabruck was carried out by one of our units." As usual in IRA statements, the declaration used the  pseudonym P O'Neill. Osnabruck, where Four Armoured Brigade is based, is the largest British base in  Germany and home to 10,700 military personnel and their families. The IRA tried to bomb the base in  1989 during a three-year terror campaign. Friday's assault raised fears that the IRA has again  switched tactics, and that despite talk of resuming the ceasefire, the organisation is planning to  step up operations.  <p>  <p>British Military Police and the German authorities have appealed for help in tracing the movements  of the white UK-registered Ford Transit truck, registration G74 OHD, used as a launch-pad. It is  thought it may have been left outside the base less than an hour before the attack.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
