 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Gazza marries Sheryl</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Gazza marries Sheryl</b><br><br><br><b><h2>  19 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Right royal  splicing</h2><h3>The wedding of the year saw Gazza finally submit to the charms of his Sheryl  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Jaci Stephen</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>As a glamour soap, it is a story that has everything. A beautiful blonde, a chunky sportsman who  weeps with sorrow and joy, and a plot crammed with all the drama of a Dallas or a Dynasty. A story of  love, separation, of thwarted ambition, recovery, disappointment, violence and power. Most importantly  of all, it is a story with a happy ending.  <p>  <p>The Gazza and Shezza epic reached its joyous climax on 1 July, and this week, the full, fluffy tale  has been captured in Hello! which had exclusive rights to the ceremony. The bride wore the kind of  frock you could venture into on safari and not see daylight before Christmas. Two hundred metres of  tulle buoyed her up over a pair of Jimmy Choo lace shoes; her bosoms, rising over the lace and beaded  cups of her bodice, looked as if they would need a separate visa to leave the country. The groom  matched her inch for inch, from the white-blond dyed hair to the brocade of his jacket and waistcoat.  They made a lovely couple. They really did. They have had their problems, both personally and  professionally, and they have come through. As Sheryl says, in the Hello! interview, they will  doubtless have many more arguments; the difference now, is that their commitment to each other will  give them the security to "resolve them and get over them". Call me naive, but I believe them. I want  to; I need to. We all do.  <p>  <p>The British are big on fairytales. In the Eighties, it was the Charles and Diana soap that  satisfied the public's insatiable need to believe that love conquers all. As they stumble towards a  divorce that has been as ugly as the union was joyous (on the outside, at least), we have lost faith  in fairytales. The marriage of Shezza and Gazza has restored it and they have taken over from the  royals as the nation's number one family. Gazza, Shezza, Bianca, Mason (Sheryl's children from a  former marriage) and Regan, her child with Gazza. God bless 'em all, and long may they reign over us.  It is not, however, a marriage made in heaven, and as fairytales go it stands somewhere between wolves  eating little girls who visit their grandmothers, and wicked witches luring children to candy houses  deep in the forest. Gazza is exceptionally volatile and has admitted taking out his frustrations on  Sheryl, which makes this a fairytale much tempered by reality.  <p>  <p>The basic fairytale plot is there, however: boy meets girl, boy loses girl, boy gets girl; or, in  Gazza's case, boy meets girl, boy loses girl, boy gets girl, boy loses girl, boy gets girl again, boy  loses girl again, etc. The only way for the boy to get the girl was to change his ways: the wild boy  had to be tamed.  <p>  <p>The Princess of Wales could have learned a lot from Sheryl, and maybe it is not too late for  Gazza's bride to be brought in as one of the Princess's confidential advisers. Get your act together  or get out, is Sheryl's philosophy; and it works.  <p>  <p>Unlike the royal story, the Gazza and Shezza show is one of unpredictability and real emotion. We  had already seen Gazza's geyser during the World Cup in Turin; last week, having held back in the  ceremony, he finally overflowed when DJ Chris Evans hugged him.  <p>  <p>The story is also one of redemption. Gazza places much of the blame for their problems on his  feelings of anger at losing his single lifestyle. Sheryl too accepts responsibility and explains her  feelings of resentment at the power she felt Gazza had over her. Sartre and de Beauvoir they ain't,  but the simple, honest way they express their self-discovery and discovery of each other makes a  refreshing change from the New Age nonsense the royals foist upon us.  <p>  <p>Gazza's joie de vivre has caused him more than a few problems, both with Sheryl and the press. The  Hello! picture of him in a urinal in his wedding clothes, champagne glass in hand, is yet further  evidence of this (as if we needed it) and the Hanbury Manor Hotel where the wedding took place, must  be thrilled that the gleam of their toilet furniture was caught so beautifully by the camera.  <p>  <p>Underneath the nonsense, however, is the story of a man who is growing up and, rather touchingly, a  man who is very much in love and not afraid to tell everyone. The Gazza and Shezza story may yet  restore the feelgood factor. And when the great man finally hangs up his football boots? He and his  new bride might make a lovely king and queen.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
