 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Tube strikes</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Tube strikes</b><br><br><br><b><h2>10 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Nine more Tube strike dates set  </h2>
  <br><br>      <p>London Underground drivers are to stage a further nine strikes in their dispute over a shorter working week, their union, Aslef, announced last night.  But Aslef's executive accepted an invitation from the conciliation service Acas to hold talks to try to avert further action. Tony West, assistant general secretary, said he hoped the "serious escalation" of the industrial action would not have to take place.  <p>  <p>Aslef cancelled a strike called for next Tuesday and set nine more dates for 24-hour walkouts: 18, 25 and 29 July; 7, 13, 23 and 27 August; and 5 and 9 September. Today the Rail, Maritime and Transport union is expected to announce that its members who are Underground drivers have voted to strike. The RMT could co-ordinate stoppages with Aslef.  <p>  <p>Mr West said Aslef regretted disruption caused by its three one-day strikes so far, but blamed LU for reneging on a deal to cut the working week by one hour.  <p>  <p>He accused management of making the situation worse by cancelling the rest days of RMT drivers on strike days and then falsely claiming that the action was crumbling. "Nothing could be further from the truth," he said. Ann Burfutt, London Transport's director of human resources, said: "We are saddened that Aslef have notified us of further dates for industrial action which could be linked to potential action by the RMT. We do, however, welcome the opportunity to get round the table at Acas."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
