 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - MPs vote to have 26 per cent salary rise</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>MPs vote to have 26 per cent salary rise</b><br><br><br><b><h2>12 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2>PM quiet on rise as MPs get car rate reprieve  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Michael White</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Downing Street last night insisted that John Major's decision whether or not to accept the MP's pay  rise which he voted against this week will be a 'private matter' for the prime minister.  <p>  <p>As union leaders renewed their criticism of the 26 per cent award voted through by a Commons  majority of 125 on Wednesday night, it also emerged that MPs will not lose their higher 74p a mile car  allowance until next April - to give them time to trade down to less 'gas guzzling' cars in future.  <p>  <p>MPs will get an extra &#163;9,000 a year before tax and ministers around &#163;17,000 each right  away because the new package ends the tradition whereby some of their MP's salary was abated when they  joined the Government.  <p>  <p>They will now get a full &#163;43,000 a year MP's salary, but will wait until after the election  before getting enhanced minister's pay which will take cabinet ministers to &#163;103,000, if they are  still in office by then.  <p>  <p>Mr Major's refusal to say whether he will take the extra money right away was matched by Tony  Blair. Other ministers and shadow ministers will not be so reluctant. Despite public anger, the size  of Wednesday's defeat for the offcial frontbench call for three per cent restraint reflects pent-up anger  on both sides that MPs have fallen behind other groups. A new anomaly emerged last night in the shape  of pay rates for ministers who are peers and thus get no pay as MPs. A parliamentary under-secertary  in the Lords will get only a &#163;1,300 pay rise, putting him or her only &#163;632 a year above a backbench MP.  <p>  <p>Postmen who deliver mail to MPs, and who will be joining strikes in a pay and working practices  dispute, yesterday attacked the politicians' bumper pay increase as 'scandalous'.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
