 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Brutal murders of Lin Russell and daughter Megan in  Kent</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Brutal murders of Lin Russell and daughter Megan in Kent</b><br><br><br><b><h2>13 July  1996</h2></b><br><h2>"Sighting" of village double killer</h2><h3>Report of man "acting furtively" provides  "deeply significant information" in hunt for murderer</h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>John Mullin</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Police believe the panic-stricken killer of Lin Russell and her six-year-old daughter, Megan, was  spotted dumping children's swimming gear in a remote lane a mile from the murder in Chillenden in  Kent.  <p>  <p>The man, acting furtively, was seen within an hour of Mrs Russell, aged 45, picking up her two  daughters from Goodnestone primary school on Tuesday. The girls had just returned from a swimming gala  in Canterbury. The witness came eye-to-eye with the suspect. Police are keen to keep his identity  secret for fear of reprisal.  <p>  <p>Josephine Russell, aged nine, remains in a critical condition in a London hospital. Police are  withholding its name for similar reasons. She suffered serious head injuries in the frenzied attack  which left her mother and younger sister dead. The family dog, Lucy, was also battered to death.  Detective Chief Inspector David Stevens, leading the investigation, believed the witness's testimony  was a breakthrough. "I consider this to be deeply significant information, vital. I think the witness  saw the murderer." The witness was walking his dog on Tuesday. As he returned to a group of houses  known as Rowling Court at 5pm, he spotted a beige coloured saloon parked in a layby, which looked like  an Escort.  <p>  <p>With Mrs Russell and her daughters last seen leaving the school at 4.10pm, the witness saw the  suspect within 50 minutes.  Mr Stevens said: "The car boot was up, and the man was trotting down the road. He stopped next to a  tree. He was looking around, acting quite suspiciously, and then he walked back to the car, and again  started to fiddle around with the boot."  <p>  <p>The witness returned home, and discussed what he had seen with his wife. There had been several  instances of puppies being dumped, and he returned to check the tree 15 minutes later. He found a net  bag, which police now know belonged to the girls. It is believed to have contained swimming towels and  one swimsuit. Police are sure the girls were carrying the bag when they left the school.  <p>  <p>The witness thought the bag was discarded rubbish. It was only when news of the murders broke the  following morning that he called police. He led them to the tree, and the bag was recovered.  <p>  <p>He described the suspect as between 35 and 40, and about 5ft 5in tall. He was slightly built, with  short, light-coloured hair.  Police believe the witness's testimony strengthens the view the killer is local. The spots where  the killings occurred and where the bag was dumped are isolated.  The bag and its contents were being analysed yesterday. Police have still to find the murder  weapon, thought to be a hammer.  <p>  <p>They believe the murders were premeditated but the getaway was botched. The suspect appeared  agitated. He looked around furtively, climbing over a bank to see if he was being watched.  The witness looked at him for about two minutes. He was about 30 metres away, and said eye contact  was made.  <p>  <p>Mrs Russell's husband, Shaun, who works at the Durrell Institute of Conservation and Research at  Kent University, was at Josephine's bedside yesterday. He is staying at a secret address in Kent.  <p>  <p>Detectives plan to interview all 2,000 residents in the three neighbouring villages of Nonington,  Chillenden and Goodnestone.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
