 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Orange parades given go-ahead in Belfast, leading to rioting  </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Orange parades given go-ahead in Belfast, leading to rioting </b><br><br><br><b><h2>12 July  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Ulster on alert for backlash</h2><h3>Orange 'victory' angers Catholics  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Sharrock</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Northern Ireland faces a further outburst of violence today with police determined to allow one of  the most emotive Orange parades in the loyalist marching calendar through a Catholic area of Belfast.  <p>  <p>With political talks falling apart under the pressure of this week's violence, Belfast was close to  boiling point last night following bloody scenes on Portadown's Garvaghy Road, where Orangemen were  finally allowed to complete their journey home from a church service five days ago. The decision by  the RUC chief constable, Sir Hugh Annesley, to let yesterday's march proceed was condemned by members  of the nationalist community as a surrender to mob rule. But John Major's ministers insisted that it  had been a purely operational matter.  <p>  <p>The Northern Ireland Secretary, Sir Patrick Mayhew, said there had been no political pressure on  Sir Hugh, who vented his frustration at having to police a hugely volatile situation with thousands of  angry people on the streets.  <p>  <p>Sir Hugh justified the reversal of his decision last Saturday to prevent the parade by effectively  admitting that loyalist violence and the sheer weight of numbers they could command had paid off and  the real danger of loss of life had become too high.  <p>  <p>He added: "I want the Government to look into the issue of how parades and demonstrations are to  run in Northern Ireland and how they can be reconciled between the two sides, because... I am sick  to death of being stuck in the middle of a non-winnable situation."  <p>  <p>Sir Patrick later said: "There needs to be guidance and therefore we will be looking very  sympathetically and urgently at some means by which an independent and external eye can be cast upon  this with a view to making recommendations."  <p>  <p>The Irish prime minister, John Bruton, and Mr Major spoke on the telephone for 20 minutes last  night. A Downing Street spokeswoman said: "They both agreed on the need for restraint on all sides,  and to find ways of stopping such occurrences happening in future."  <p>  <p>But a statement issued by a Dublin government spokesman said: "The Taoiseach told the Prime  Minister that there was widespread anger and deep concern in Ireland about the decision to allow the  Orange march down the Garvaghy Road, a decision on which there was no advance notice or consultation.  "The Taoiseach also told the Prime Minister he was dismayed that the elaborate preparations which were  made to prevent this provocative march were simply thrown aside in the face of massive intimidation."  As the march moved down Garvaghy Road, riot police fired plastic bullets at protesters and batoned  others staging a sit-down in the path of the parade. About 1,300 Orangemen marched to a drum beat,  ignoring the petrol bombs, rocks and abuse of residents.  <p>  <p>Within hours of the Garvaghy skirmishes and with violence erupting in nationalist areas of Belfast,  Armagh and Londonderry, more than 50 RUC armoured Land Rovers moved into Belfast's Ormeau Road in  preparation for today's Twelfth of July parade, putting the largely Catholic area under a 16-hour  curfew.  <p>  <p>The move came as an application by the nationalist Lower Ormeau Concerned Community for a judicial  review of today's parade by an Orange Lodge making its way to the main Belfast march - the highpoint  of the Battle of the Boyne anniversary celebrations - was rejected by the High Court.  <p>  <p>Spokesman Gerard Rice said: "The RUC are powerless, Mayhew is powerless and the courts are  powerless... Thousands of RUC men are swamping this area and beating people off the streets. It's  Orange law."  <p>  <p>The father of the Catholic taxi driver Michael McGoldrick who was murdered early on Monday by  unidentified gunmen yesterday said he had forgiven his son's killers. Urging an end to violence, he  said: "As I bury my son, bury your pride."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
