 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Orange parades given go-ahead in Belfast, leading to rioting </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Orange parades given go-ahead in Belfast, leading to rioting </b><br><br><br><b><h2>24 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Politicians seek cool heads for Londonderry parades  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Peter Hetherington</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Nationalists and loyalists in Londonderry have held informal meetings in an attempt to avoid widespread disorder during the annual Apprentice Boys parade in the city next month.  <p>  <p>Amid fears of a repetition of the province-wide rioting following an Orange parade through Garvaghy Road in Portadown two weeks ago, John Hume, leader of the Social Democratic and Labour Party (SDLP), has met the head of the Apprentice Boys to defuse tempers in Londonderry.  <p>  <p>With local republicans planning to march through the mainly Protestant Waterside area of the city on Thursday night, loyalists appear determined to assert what they regard as a traditional right to parade around the city's recently restored walls on the 10 August parade. They then plan to join more than 12,000 other Orangemen to march through the Protestant enclave of the Fountain on the way to St Colomb's Church of Ireland Cathedral. Both the Ulster Unionist leader, David Trimble, and Ian Paisley, leader of the Democratic Unionist Party, have visited Londonderry to stress they see no need to change the route, which will pass above the nationalist Bogside area. But the local SDLP believes a compromise will be needed to re-route the march from the Bogside if trouble is to be avoided.  <p>  <p>Incensed by the RUC's decision to allow the Portadown march down the Garvaghy Road, some nationalists are threatening to block the Craigavan Bridge over the Foyle to stop the Apprentice Boys crossing into the old city.  <p>  <p>With battle lines being drawn, Sir Patrick Mayhew, the Northern Ireland Secretary, is preparing to meet the Apprentice Boys to reach a compromise. Mr Hume is also planning further talks with Alastair Simpson, the governor of the Apprentice Boys.  Their annual event commemorates the 13 boys who slammed the gates in the face of the deposed Catholic king James II in 1688.  <p>  <p>The DUP's security spokesman, Gregory Campbell, a member of the Apprentice Boys, insisted yesterday the parade must follow its traditional route. The right to parade around the walls was not up for negotiation. Mark Durkan, of the SDLP, who accompanied Mr Hume, said people had been meeting at "different levels". But he cautioned: "What is really missing is direct dialogue."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
