 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - PM set for 60,000 rise as Commons gets free vote on pay </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>PM set for 60,000 rise as Commons gets free vote on pay </b><br><br><br><b><h2>  19 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2> PM set for 60,000 rise as Commons gets free vote on pay  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Hencke</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Huge pay rises for MPs and ministers  <p>  <p>including a &#163;60,000 annual increase for the next prime minister - are to be rushed through Parliament next week.  <p>  <p>A free vote for MPs to approve a &#163;9,000 increase for backbenchers and pay rises of between &#163;20,000 and &#163;30,000 for ministers is  <p>  <p>expected to be agreed by the Cabinet today. The rises would be the biggest for more than 30 years, but will not come into force until after the next election.  <p>  <p>Tony Blair, who could benefit from the biggest rise in the prime minister's pay this century if he enters Downing Street, declined yesterday to reveal which way he will vote. So did John Major. But Paddy Ashdown, the Liberal Democrat leader, is to vote against and will back a 3 per cent rise. Details of the pay rises were revealed yesterday with the leaking to the Press Association of a Senior Staff Salaries Review Board report, which calls for substantial rises to redress a long period in which MPs' pay has been tied to inflation.  <p>  <p>The report recommends salaries of &#163;103,000 per year for cabinet ministers and the Speaker, an increase of more than &#163;33,000 on the present &#163;69,651 a year. Ministers of state would receive &#163;74,125 and junior ministers &#163;66,623, rises of between &#163;15,000 and  <p>  <p>&#163; 20,000 a year.  <p>  <p>The report, however, criticised the mileage rates paid to MPs and recommended a substantial cut. It describes the top rate, 74.1p, as 'unjustifiably generous' and recommends the level paid to peers, 47.2p a mile.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
