 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Bomb goes off at Olympics site, Atlanta's Centennial Park</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Bomb goes off at Olympics site, Atlanta's Centennial Park</b><br><br><br><b><h2>  19 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2> Games in shadow of terror  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>John Duncan</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>FBI investigators said yesterday they were closing in on the terrorist who detonated a bomb in Atlanta's Centennial Park during the early hours of Saturday morning, as officials scrambled to explain why a warning received by emergency operators never reached the park where thousands of revellers were attending a rock concert.  <p>  <p>Investigators confirmed they were looking for "a white American man" who made a warning call to police 18 minutes before the blast. An FBI spokesman, David Tubbs, said composite sketches of at least one suspect could be released soon. The warning call came from a public telephone outside a hotel adjoining the park. The phone had been taken to Washington for forensic tests, Mr Tubbs said.  <p>  <p>The blast, which sent nails and screws flying into the crowd, killed an American woman, and a Turkish cameraman died of a heart attack as he rushed to the scene. It injured 110 people.  <p>  <p>FBI sources said the pipe-bomb was more sophisticated than initially thought, but that agents were still concentrating on the theory that a local terrorist was responsible. The device was being compared to "other bombs built over the course of the years in this country".  <p>  <p>As the Games continued and attendances at most events remained high, President Clinton hailed athletes and spectators for showing "that they would not be intimidated". He said he had invited congressional leaders to the White House today to discuss expanding wiretapping and chemically 'tagging' explosives to help crack down on terrorism.  <p>  <p>Games organisers said the Centennial Park, designed to be the life and soul of the Olympics, would reopen tomorrow with boosted security, including random bag searches.  <p>  <p>Meanwhile investigators probing the crash of a TWA Boeing 747 off eastern Long Island on 17 July, killing all 230 people aboard, were speculating that the explosion was caused by a bomb in the front cargo section, one of them told Associated Press.  <p>  <p>The theory emerged after officials revealed they had found the front section of the aircraft more than 1 1/2 miles from debris from the rest of the plane.  <p>  <p>"I guess it's fair to say that things that come off first tend to be an indicator of what happened," said Robert Francis, the vice-chairman of the National Transportation Safety Board.  <p>  <p>Atlanta's mayor, Bill Campbell, said investigators were hoping to identify the Olympic bomber from television footage of the explosion and videos taken by surveillance cameras.  <p>  <p>Police confirmed that no other devices had been found.  <p>  <p>Atlanta officials came under pressure to explain why the warning call made to an emergency operator at 1.07am failed to reach the park before the device exploded at 1.25am.  <p>  <p>The knapsack containing the bomb was coincidentally spotted by a policeman minutes before it exploded. Agents were moving people away when the blast occurred.  <p>  <p>The city's police chief, Beverley Harvard, said that an officer was dispatched to 'secure' the payphone before the warning was passed to a unit that co-ordinated responses to bomb threats.  <p>  <p>She said the warning reached the unit at about the time the bomb exploded, but insisted police could not have responded quicker because the warning was not sufficiently specific. "The caller only stated that there was a bomb in the park with no location at all, and basically said you have 30 minutes." For a second day yesterday Atlanta was hit by a wave of bomb scares and hoax calls as the Games continued.  <p>  <p>A sombre International Olympic Committee president, Juan Antonio Samaranch, said he was impressed with the efforts of security forces in the moments before the blast and satisfied that the Games security was tight. "We are very grateful to the authorities for their excellent response and for the security measures they have taken," he said.  <p>  <p>Media speculation about the identity of the bomber has focussed on America's shady network of so-called militia groups. Two members of a local rightwing group were charged in April with plotting a bombing campaign, though Olympic organisers denied that the two had planned to target the Games. Yesterday, however, a spokesman for the self-styled '112th Regiment Militia-at-Large for the Republic of Georgia' insisted that the group had no connection with the attack. "We want to say that we had nothing whatsoever to do with this and we hope that whoever did this is caught as soon as possible," J. J. Johnson said.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
