 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Tories launch negative electioneering campaigns against Labour </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Tories launch negative electioneering campaigns against Labour </b><br><br><br><b><h2>  19 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2> Central Office "fears and smears" alarm Labour  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Michael White</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>A jittery Labour Party last night launched a ferocious attack on the Conservatives' election strategy in the wake of new evidence that Central Office will be spending a record &#163;10m on an American-style  negative campaign of "fears and smears".  <p>  <p>After the Conservative chairman, Dr Brian Mawhinney, launched a poster bearing the slogan "Labour's Union Jack" over a white flag with the message "New Labour. No Britain" Labour strategists summoned a press conference to reject Dr Mawhinney's charge that Scots, Welsh and English regional assemblies - plus an elected all-London authority - would cost &#163;108m a year. This was a "factually inaccurate and dishonest smear", shadow chancellor Gordon Brown said yesterday.  <p>  <p>But the attack which has especially alarmed Labour was last Thursday's party political broadcast by the Conservatives. A sinister pair of eyes - associated with the new Saatchi slogan "New Labour, New Danger" - were seen peering through a curtain, a computer screen or even bank cash dispenser to threaten voters' savings.  <p>  <p>One former Tory cabinet who saw the broadcast said yesterday: "A party of government which can run a broadcast like that has lost all sense of decency and deserves a spell of opposition."  <p>  <p>Mr Brown yesterday challenged John Major "to say whether he has given his personal go-ahead for the unrelenting and unremitting negative campaign based around a series of big lies".  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></t