 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Flight TWA 800 blown up </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Flight TWA 800 blown up </b><br><br><br><b><h2>19 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2>The loss of Flight 800 -  US crash investigators resist bomb speculation</h2><h3>The TWA tragedy raises many questions  about security on flights</h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Fairhall</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Experts working to discover what brought down TWA Flight 800 are resisting speculation that might  distort their investigation.  <p>  <p>James Hall, chairman of the United States National Transportation Safety Board, said yesterday it  was vital that they "follow the facts". But their search is based - like all the speculation - on a  process of seeking answers to a series of questions:  <p>  <p>Why should a Boeing 747 jumbo jet explode shortly after take-off - something that has never  happened?  <p>  <p>There are two main possibilities: a mechanical failure leading to fire and an explosion - or  sabotage in the form of a terrorist bomb.  <p>  <p>What sort of mechanical failure might be involved?  <p>  <p>Aircraft engines do sometimes catch fire and/or explode, particularly at the high-power settings  used for take-off and the initial climb. When mounted on the wings - as in the Boeing 747 - this could  rupture and ignite the main kerosene fuel tanks within, leading to the sort of 'fireball' reported by  witnesses to the latest crash.  <p>  <p>There have also been incidents involving 747s in which an engine fell off. The most serious  occurred four years ago involving an El Al cargo plane which subsequently crashed in Amsterdam.  <p>  <p>Why was the flight's take-off delayed for an hour on Wednesday evening? An early unconfirmed report  suggested ground crews replaced an engine pressure-ratio gauge which indicates the power setting - the  equivalent of a sports car's rev counter.  <p>  <p>In theory, this should have no effect on the plane's performance, but there could have been some  serious side-effect. TWA said the flight was delayed to identify an unclaimed item of baggage and  remove a broken-down motorised baggage loader.  <p>  <p>Is the fact that this was an old aircraft significant?  <p>  <p>In general, airliners become safer as they settle down into service. Crews become familiar with the  equipment and mechanical bugs are ironed out. The Boeing jumbo has an exceptional safety record.  However, this particular plane was one of the first 747s to enter service, an aircraft which first  flew 25 years ago. At such an age, problems do sometimes surface. Did the pilot send out any distress  call?  <p>  <p>Apparently not, despite early reports that the coastguard heard something. This is a strong reason  for suspecting there was a bomb on board. What other indications are there?  <p>  <p>The intense fireball reported by witnesses, again suggesting a bomb explosion. However, one witness  said the plane spiralled down before exploding, which ties in with the possibility of mechanical  failure. Will the answer be found?  <p>  <p>Almost certainly. US Navy divers were confident last night that they would be able to recover at  least one of the 'black boxes' - a cockpit voice recorder and a flight data recorder - which, if  undamaged, would give an account of any aircraft failure. Bodies, seats and baggage will be examined  for metal fragments and traces of explosive.  <p>  <p>If it was a bomb, how did it get on board?  <p>  <p>Most likely in baggage which was checked in - perhaps at another airport - so as to avoid human  scrutiny and evade explosives-sniffing sensors. The device could be triggered by a barometric device  (the plane had reached 13,000ft) or by a timer.  <p>  <p>If so, can anything be done to prevent such outrages?  <p>  <p>Yes, but at a cost in disruption and, ultimately, higher fares. 'Soft' airports have to be  hardened, as Athens - an earlier departure point for this aircraft - is supposed to have been.  <p>  <p>British defence scientists at Farnborough, meanwhile, have developed a system of protective blast  screens and reinforcement which they believe would contain a baggage-hold blast of the kind that  destroyed the Pan Am 747 over Lockerbie in 1988.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
</DOC>
